column3: Landmark eatery, newly renovated, offering a New American menu & stunning views of Manhattan.
column8: 1 Water St, Brooklyn, NY 11201, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Nicole Montana","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100393296380587706574/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxZOtRCUA1ZPCsDmru7lHUWxd0iBmdfOgu69PUnL=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"From my arrival to the end of the meal, the staff was amazing! So friendly, professional, and polite. The food is delicious and the presentation is top-tier. The amazing views are definitely another reason to dine here. I mean who doesn’t want to say they’ve basically fine dined under the Brooklyn bridge?! From birthdays to anniversaries, The River Café  is a restaurant well worth a visit. Just be sure to book in advance, you’ll be thankful you did.","time":1646018008,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Jennifer Winthurst","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106162101732514347568/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SGUwlv6AXQ9nY5AAODuxQUssbO8wHHRw2HTtAbmJE=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"5 months ago","text":"Superb! They made us feel like queens and kings. The staff was outstanding. The  walk in was beautiful. They have fall lights, flowers and a little water fountain. It's definitely an experience. While at dinner I looked left and looked at the Brooklyn bridge. Then to my right in the distance was the Statue of Liberty. The whole night was fabulous. Went here to celebrate my fiance birthday. Great place for birthdays or any occasion. They also had a wedding reception going on too. The only bad thing I could say is their chairs are not comfortable. They're wicker chairs.","time":1667012191,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Sarah","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110233785076574988768/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxbELFXr7fpArTTqQZ25BvAE1GHpYi5UYxjRa2GI=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"From arrival to leaving, amazing, staff were friendly, professional, and polite. The range of cocktails both with or without alcohol were amazing.... the menu.. well.. simply everything we had was succulent, vibrant, tasty and meticulously prepared, presented, and served. So so pleased we booked well in advance... thank you for a wonderful and memorable evening on my first, but will not the the last visit to NYC/River Cafe.","time":1643290402,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Allison S","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101018885838779545541/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RaHuJbP9m8tT2ai9_bSu7vjvdoDmdCqWMi4sZAWQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"My husband and I came here to celebrate our 2 year anniversary, and we had an unforgettable experience! The views alone make this place worth a visit for a special occasion, but other than that, the food and drinks were also wonderful.

I will say, be fully prepared to spend a lot of money, but I do think it’s worth it. The menu is a fixed price menu ($180 per person which included an appetizer, entree, dessert, and some chef samples along the way), so definitely look into that on their website before you go. There is also a dress code (jackets for men, etc.).

The staff was so kind and attentive, and they made us feel very special on our anniversary, even bringing out a dessert that had “Happy Anniversary” written on it. This was truly the most memorable dining experience we have ever had. We highly recommend this place to anyone and everyone!","time":1656442523,"translated":false},{"author_name":"APHW “Planeteer”","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114819216901345355210/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RmhW7ToI7Yxdqfnn4_z7jJ07O_TAtqz6AZx8o_kA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"Wonderful service and delicious food! The timing of courses and drinks are impeccable! The nighttime scenery is beautiful at any time of year because the city is always lit. The lights on the grotto provide a romantic little walk. Walkway can be slippery when raining.","time":1654655931,"translated":false}]

Loved seeing Amy Sherald portraits here.","time":1571250867,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Alex Amidon","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114562255876740968383/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TZ3wzPvz6MvXTcl31pMf-SLh2IXPeLDs_D9lyOng=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"6 years ago","text":"Professional, friendly not snooty. (Do get the homemade sodas: rosemary lemon is refreshingly thirst-quenching without being too sweet.)","time":1485727250,"translated":false}]

column3: Townhouse art gallery with a wide-ranging roster that runs from Francis Bacon to Andy Warhol.
column8: 20 E 79th St, New York, NY 10075, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"A O","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105707669582831172745/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QUDckTFK47GS9aR8eNQSbh8bzyvsRRusU4fGwfVmM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 years ago","text":"Stops in for the Kaws Gone exhibit during the week and happy that we did. column3: Works by well-known contemporary artists take center stage at this airy exhibition space.
column8: 525 W 19th St, New York, NY 10011, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Michael Tcheyan","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100015079310374862633/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RGJkThQZcv-0nvh7bfPogmlZzEMx67_QxCBT8u3Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"One of the four mega galleries there's currently an extraordinary exhibition on at David Zwirner.  This is the work of the 86-year-old British artist Rose Wiley.  Definitely not a show to be missed I urge you to go see it.  Attached are a few pictures.","time":1621743975,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Janet","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112410994063859886710/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QHfrCOrA4bgZqGBTdDm1oLVR9jUbeSLjPHm_sehw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 years ago","text":"Went to the Kusama exhibit and was definitely not disappointed. Lines may be long, but well-organized by the team at the gallery — especially wonderful when you consider this is a free art exhibit open to all. I went on a very cold morning about 30 min before the gallery opened and waited about another 30 min to get in. I believe you can bypass the line if you are not interested in the infinity mirrored room. As most people choose to see it, the limited flow from the room to the rest of the exhibit means you mostly have lots of personal space and time to enjoy the other installations!","time":1574800289,"translated":false},{"author_name":"James Prather","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109535878072091258702/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QlxW6wYEMeCA20ajVKek8dMKPNG0k9QCfV4Yplcw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 years ago","text":"This gallery is spacious, providing room to appreciate the art of Noah Davis, a young black man who passed away at the age of 32 from a rare tissue cancer.

Noah's snapshots of life covers both the intimate family pictures, landscapes, and the ethereal.

Also showing in the gallery was an experimental artist named Doug Wheeler. You are treated to a giant room filled with a soft light, emminating from the back.

A great place to visit, along with the many other galleries on the street, for tourists looking for free art.","time":1580594406,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ahmad AbouZanat","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106816829325315415784/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Qz4T3Sae7-0h5pTNtP73okd39K9XwwAdtOpB_FdQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 years ago","text":"Probably the best gallery in New York City. It’s a bit crowded sometimes but the gallery is big and there’s room for so many.

Their installations include paintings; sculptures, spaces, sound installations...etc

The circulation in the space is easy and the staff is very friendly and organized. One of my favorite places to visit with and without clients.","time":1581739346,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Peter Liu","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100643109161309918309/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxbgVP2tO0lgbnmf1XzxATvJyhUP7NE6ujyRP6zL=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"5 years ago","text":"Very nice gallery. Professional, efficient, fun. We were there for Yayoi Kusama exhibits.  The lines were around the corner but staff was kind and courteous giving direction and ushering ppl from one area to the next.  Fun experience.","time":1512603108,"translated":false}]

It’s the perfect walk in bar with no reservations. It’s tucked away quietly behind some loud clubs.

It’s a nicely decorated space and definitely a good spot for a drink after dinner or for a date.

You go to the bar to order drinks. They have some infused liquor drinks that are delicious. Would recommend for a small group","time":1676864761,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ariel Aviles","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100425782858340841462/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Tq430WmHn6-OMT-x2-7IEb6l_BNbtWWkz7i-a0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Best bar in the East Village!  We have been going for a few years, this past weekend we went Thursday, Saturday and Sunday!  We are not from NYC, but we travel there very often.

The beef:  It is a small, dark, cosy little bar, perfect for a date!  Their cocktail menu has excellent options, all refreshing and great examples of friendly mixology!  The bartender "Zoey" is amazing, super friendly and surprisingly fast!  Music is really cool!

I see some negative comments and I think you need to evaluate venues in categories, and Lovers of Today is meant to be small, tight, dark and cosy... its not a big bar, so don't expect big bar amenities.  This is a gem in the East Village, we will keep visiting and recommending to all of our friends!!!","time":1655833655,"translated":false},{"author_name":"byron subero","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102791184982364311448/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Rw4mLi3PR0JGkBQ_GZfDO4WPTUF4pPJBoz7z6cvQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"The last speakeasy I went to while in NYC. column3: Family-owned shop offering high-end smoked fish, caviar & New York-style specialty foods since 1914.
column8: 179 E Houston St, New York, NY 10002, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Alberto Gallegos","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117708666366409722402/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Q7mgJSoNRrhYyUp0WoyeRGc09zJHPXXEi603rBbA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"Delicious & wonderful. Everything bagel plus the lox cream cheese were great. They also sell some delicious fresh squeezed orange juice. I say get there a lil early if you can, because the line forms quick; but if not, no big deal because they move pretty fast. You take a number & wait your turn. Definitely worth going & trying & definitely worth returning.","time":1665183312,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Wilfred Tam","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104865202923001598706/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TNmXArkvtQXtGMPhKRsCvm601GADLqYEfZi1qBfUA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":3,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"Beautifully preserved bagel shop that’s been open for over 100 years. Went on a Monday morning and got a ticket at 10am, about 32 people in line ahead of us. Line moved quite fast. Probably 30 min wait. Ordered the meshugge and a daughters.
Tasty bagels and smoked salmon. Total was about 50$.
Very friendly service.
Good bagel, though nothing that special about the bagel or smoked salmon that would make it worth the wait or price.
I’d say 90% of people in line were tourists probably checking out the hype.","time":1670902127,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ron de Leon","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111233722373794848870/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QnGaL_CMnRWW-peb-SrEEBQm4aFn_1oheHBZjE9uM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"a month ago","text":"I’ve got “The Classic” from their menu. It’s bagel with salmon and cream cheese. We had it to go and ate it in a nearby Starbucks. The salmon and cream cheese are really good but the bagel is somewhat hard to bite. I don’t know if it’s because I didn’t eat it immediately and we had to walk for quite sometime in a cold weather that made the bagel a bit hard. I’ll probably gonna get it again once I’m back in new york.","time":1676256282,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Warakorn M","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113846479896540928477/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5S4liS62nAsGmZcdyLDFMdpx67DD-9urnpxfReCmg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"I had a salmon lox bagel sandwich with cream cheese. It was delicious. We wait for approx 30 min.  It was ok for me I enjoyed the atmosphere and different sections of the store. Staffs are polite and nice. Staffs are nice.
We have to walk a bit to find a place to sit down and eat.","time":1672527333,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Rita Ramalhete","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111601034348647946655/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QkVP4Nbt1kTrvnF-Wdq1ainBRdUNIb24kETS7UUhY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"Very cute deli serving bagels with a great range of fillings, from cream cheese spreads to different types of smoked fish. The bagels were top notch and their salmon is amazing. They also sell canned goods, a few sweet treats and coffee.","time":1652706823,"translated":false}]

column3: undefined
column8: 461 W Broadway, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11: [{"author_name":"Adam Wetzel","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109930203218472588968/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxafCtDlonLrLU_2VyQQBK-orAtaGY5_RCNgIFRR=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"2 years ago","text":"Authentic Pre-Owned is a Must-See-To-Believe shop in Soho. Even if I wasn't into hard-to-find and one-of-a-kind collectibles, this store is amazing for what knowledge Bobby (the owner) will dispense to the people who visit; every time I go in, I come out a smarter man! The store has collectible, vintage timepieces (some previously owned by well-known leaders); signage (American; European, etc.); luggage (think Hermes; Louis Vuitton...); vintage doll-head molds; fur coats...I have made several purchases from Bobby (see images of some items) and his eagerness to make a sale is part of the fun for me. All the items I have acquired from the shop are in amazing condition and arrive to me in the same condition as when I saw them and purchased them due to Bobby's fine care in packaging. I will be back to the store the next time I'm in Manhattan!!","time":1591645564,"translated":false},{"author_name":"John Vairo","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105288812879519759708/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxYoppbl_BH4DK3EERGtS3BGOVyWybc2_BujDx1U=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"2 years ago","text":"Aptiques is a hidden gem here in NYC that everyone should visit. The collection in the store (and now online) is rare, exquisite and unique. For years, I was looking for an apothecary cabinet that had a specifically tall and narrow dimension. I searched high and low across the U.S. and never in my wildest dreams did I think I would find it in NYC at Aptiques—and for an affordable price no less. Not only did I buy the apothecary cabinet but on a later visit, I purchased two vintage midcentury Hubley cap guns in heavy metal from a larger collection of them—holsters and all. What drew me into the store initially was a giant black surf board with the Chanel logo placed prominently across the center of the board. When I walked in I was dazzled by the rare architectural salvage, photography, art, jewelry, objects d'art, vintage clothing, motorcycle jackets and a giant punching bag made out of a Louis Vuitton leather print among other many extraordinary things curated throughout the space! I just recently purchased a third vintage Hubley Colt 45 cap gun from the same collection as the two guns I purchased prior. Aptiques modified this Colt 45 Hubley with a Louis Vuitton print on the handle! To say that I'm over the moon with this unique piece is an understatement. I feel like the new Sheriff in town—the town of Luxuryville that is. This place is amazing and the owner is a gentleman and a professional with endless knowledge and passion for the things he has collected and is selling. Support the businesses that truly make New York City a unique place. Aptiques is definitely one of those places!","time":1595353500,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Dd Tree","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116626050966828542657/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxYmw7HaVsHMDsXY7OyoCJ7hWHmt8j0hSL92WII0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Walking into Bobby's store for the first time was a truely a magical experience. There isn't any store in the world to compare it to. It is so rare to see a person with such passion. Bobby is one of a kind and an amazing beautiful person. His store is perfectly curated almost like being in a museum of the most fantastic collections that one can only dream about. He goes out of his way to spend time with every customer and has always allowed me to purchase items giving me great prices and making me feel like a million bucks! I encourage anyone to go there and I promise it will be an experience of a lifetime. Thank you Bobby for allowing me to appreciate you and your store. Your kindness is exuberant!","time":1654974059,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Adam Nathan","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112756684545298657746/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Qi-rkPN3D0hhcwDPG89J3_22KoPyL8vaoUj59b8w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"It's a bit of a Wonderland inside the shop. Beautifully curated and eclectic. Massive Annie Liebowitz volumes. Vintage typewriters. A Beefeater. You can spend some time in here.\n\nI came home with a Lionel train set from the 1930's. Couldn't be happier. A real find and a great destination during a trip to SoHo.","time":1631572779,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Don Ackad","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112702448071764787476/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TgUkdb8qvdkbtDN8tP6c7FgeGfPLfGH1-GWEyaPg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"2 years ago","text":"Super friendly and what a collection!  I was looking a vintage gift and had several amazing items to choose from!  Will be coming back again!  I highly recommend this shop!","time":1597244059,"translated":false}]

column3: Sister to the Chicago original serving elevated burgers & American dishes in a stylish setting.
column8: 33 Cortlandt Alley, New York, NY 10013, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Joshua Dyer","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118232179344071940672/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TkRaY2Dqi89dw7mmIQjy_gHGOzysQwzhZjvCnFRg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Really dope restaurant with a great ambiance. Definitely a top tier spot to grab a burger. Make sure you put your reservation in or you might not get seated. The service was great. The burger was absolutely delicious and cooked to perfection. The egg and thick cut bacon really topped it off. The combination of all those flavors was mouth watering. The fries weren’t bad, I got the egg on the fries just to be extra and see if it gives a unique taste but it’s not a necessity.","time":1656206331,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Spencer Nord","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103591431097451195554/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RuQkO46CGOjls2pIopbQAv-VBz8Edy2yLgl37r=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"Great meal. Au Cheval has great ambience and a simple yet refined menu that will leave you totally stuffed. The staff was A+ and we didn’t need to ask for a thing — they were always one step ahead! The bacon is a true highlight here. You get what you pay for, so it’s a bit pricey but we’ll worth a visit.","time":1661092497,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Xavier Bunyan","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106206267603704001666/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RqTkabZdltBROeLP4137lPr2vFBG_xHF9GY3MAaQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a month ago","text":"Came here for brunch, we ordered the Avocado Toast with egg, Kale Salad, Simple Breakfast, Cheeseburger and a side of bacon. Everything tasted fresh and was perfectly cooked. Staff was very friendly and attentive and frequently checked in with us to see if the food and drinks were to our liking. The eggs in the Simple Breakfast were perfectly cooked with the right amount of chives. I definitely liked that everything was properly seasoned and I didn't have to add salt or pepper after getting my order.","time":1676877351,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Shauna Gonzalez","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109946883409449536241/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Tf9gKqYHKPYH7R7miHItkCQX_vggCfFusyJO9WxA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"Loved the ambiance and the food. The chopped wedge salad was amazing and I loved the burger. For a textural component it would be nice to have crispy bacon rather than thick steakhouse style. We had a bit of a mixed bag with service, some where abrupt and short with us and others very friendly.","time":1670400587,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Shaun Young","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100583678184344629465/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TIWBrZForOopB2zUc8JR8Nhh62pw__BI2X_MDNoQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"Au Cheval is really good. We went for a birthday brunch and everyone in the group enjoyed their food and drink.

The highlights were the chilaquiles, omelet, hash browns and green salad. The paper thin pickles piled atop the Bloody Mary were a great addition to the traditional garnish of olives and hot pepper.

The service was warm and friendly; the space the same.

I look forward to returning and exploring more of the menu.","time":1664882097,"translated":false}]

column3: Old-time bar with Irish bartenders, 2 kinds of ale (light or dark) & sawdust on the floor.
column8: 15 E 7th St, New York, NY 10003, USA
column11: [{"author_name":"Mark Fahmy","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116455970340986901319/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxYlhR1N1lfN35CzuYxeQuRRlZCXYRHOeeFhvzTWgF8=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Came here with a group and this was our last stop in a nights pub crawl. This was the birthday boys favorite pub and I can see why. This pubs history is so rich and it was so nice to see it displayed all over the pub. The beer is simple whether you want light beer or dark beer. The fries were good and I also ordered the hot dog which filled my craving. The service was great even though they were quite busy on a Friday night. We were a group of 6 and we were able to get a table. Would definitely come here again as it’s such a great way to end the night.","time":1659130050,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Raj Bhatia","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105201237159414968086/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RkjsFupnhb4677PWEQfQaVcRnVDHg1yYBuLz5N1A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Hands downs single best place on the planet. I’ve been coming here since 1985 and love it more each time. I especially love the fact that nothing changes -  The people the food and the decor. This is special special place with a deep history. It’s part museum and part ale house and there’s a story to be told about each and every item on the walls and behind the bar. The staff is special as well and most have been there for decades..really. Do yourself and go right now… But don’t ask for anything for a light or dark beer, and if you want to sound like a regular ask for “two and two.”  God bless Mcsorleys!","time":1641758136,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Vinnie 1973","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108306559901049230910/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5T6WyxjJRqfTKa6aM1576wyTg6cFWZ_ViPl98xU6g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"Can't go to NY without a trip to McSorleys!!  It's so much fun!!  You will meet people, enjoy stories; food as simple as crackers and Mister Mustard with raw onions and cheese.  My dad used to enjoy this concoction watching football when I was a kid so it brings back fond memories. They also have burger, hot dog or chicken sandwich. Beer is cheapest in the City...light or dark two for one 🍻","time":1672147835,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Terence McConlogue","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106727604895078318356/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RHs1Npgjj-bSJavfnoQ6qHlT7bokjzkt_l5kyN3g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"If you can’t give this place five stars just for the fact it survived I don’t wanna be your friend!  Only two beers, dark or light, poured in the same manner they were 100 years ago, so lots of head, never a full beer.  They’ve even kept many of the original menu items such as the liverwurst sandwich that is truly a classic.  Served with brilliant fresh white onion and mustard that will blow your sinuses up it CANNOT be beat.  Just do yourself a favor and go…you won’t be sorry","time":1670090111,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Tiki Fhe","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112832672034475439784/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxYR-hEw7TVZCo_ScRM50LTBkRWpwap4ymJTx9RX=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"Finally got to visit after someone recommended this place to me years ago.\nSafe to say, there's a reason this place is incredible.\nSuch a buzz, especially when going around after work hours. The light one is refreshing and the waiters super attentive in replenishing when you're empty. Plus surprisingly affordable. A must when in Downtown!","time":1653010988,"translated":false}]

column3: Since 1961, many famous artist have played at this iconic music club with nightly shows & cocktails.
column8: 147 Bleecker St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11: [{"author_name":"Praveen Sr","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111502475592381744159/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5S0c3lMpNVdWZJsSMGwmqbdQ5_3D6nVUi0hBuUC-Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"Apparently one of New York's oldest rock clubs, established in 1961. Bob Dylan, Joni Mitchell have all had performances here. column3: French bistro & wine bar presenting duck confit, lamb & other savory fare in a romantic setting.
column8: 18 Cornelia St #1, New York, NY 10014, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Mark Mangrich","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114559533420120102624/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TPs5Z41Dn1Mt6mMIdSIRAAVIRD9X7UuaPOYzw-iQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"We were a party of 8. We took up an entire section of this cute and quaint little place. They had a large selection of specials that were not on the menu that our server explained to us. We ordered wine, starters, mains and dessert with coffee. Everything was great. The escargot is amazing. I had risotto with shrimp and crab. It was rich, but exactly what I was looking for. The desserts were great too. The restaurant is small but you feel like family there. They pay careful attention to your food and experience. The neighborhood is safe and off the beaten path.","time":1672326181,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Rits M","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105274745562535635389/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5R1mhDMekExErDYNN8LnhcVcc5q2n-SuRMx0wHQrQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":3,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Unfortunately a very forgettable meal for me.

I came here for dinner. We were seated outdoors immediately. They have some indoor seating - about 8 tables mostly for couples. Outside they have about 5 tables in the summer.

The service was relatively slow and since the menu didn't have too many options I was hoping all the food that they did they would do well. From menu to leaving we ordered about 3 dishes and it took 2.5 hours.

At best the food was fresh but it wasn't either tasty or memorable. It didn't have either flavor complexity or interest in terms of ingredient combination. I would probably come here for a basic meal but at the prices I expected something a little more upscale I suppose. We tried the heirloom tomato salad, the crab cake and the ravioli.

I would pass on this place for dinner - might be a better lunch option to be fair","time":1638582904,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Arthur W. Allen","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114723005363458949810/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxYiCSxoFp36IPEV40WFC3p0x9kwzc5JWseBFDR9=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"11 months ago","text":"Favorite Village dining experience. It reminded us of our time in Paris.  It's small, cozy and intimate space with excellent service.  The food was also outstanding.  We will definitely go back.","time":1675084681,"translated":false}]

column3: Pastries, fresh bread & celebrated oversized cookies in a relaxed spot that has counter seating.
column8: 340 Lafayette St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Hope ALM","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112008567503490942516/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TKpxo-WcveN56wTpeqrzi9rvYdU82ySvyh6TNstQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"What is not to love here😝. My favorite is their dark chocolate peanut butter. To my palate, that is unsurpassed cookie that has peanut butter. They have other delicious stuff of course. I just swear by this creation. Ive tried several cookie places, especially when i am craving their peanut butter one, but sadly there have been no substitute. I used to trek over to their Upper West Side location, but I am glad I am now closer to their NoHo location. They have space to eat your goodies indoors. No seating though. Service is super quick, but when there is a line, your wait will be worth it. I highly recommend trying them out. Oh also, they have hiked their prices. My favorite used to be $4; it is now $5. Same hefty chunk of goodness though😝. Enjoy!","time":1664120370,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Carson Wong","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116193403908839881454/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SfFjIHEVIdF2xo4kk8P_dg-i4bPthe6V4xKhc7_w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"A solid high-quality cookie that is a must-try if you're in the area, but I wouldn't say that you're missing out on too much if you've never tried it. We ordered the double chocolate chip and the chocolate walnut cookies and both were crunchy on the outside, soft and gooey on the inside filled with lots of chocolate but a tad bit oily on the inside for my liking. In terms of flavour nothing was mind boggling - it tasted like a really good chocolate chip cookie. However, the decor and overall aesthetic of the store is very clean and pleasant and the service was helpful and nice. Again, would recommend you try it at least once if you're in the area.","time":1653749203,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Karina Lam","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100449351363856550855/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RwopKSndWgU_mSlzrmKfWoqhaW4ylDViapzOdPug=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"11 months ago","text":"I lived in NYC my entire life, but I never got a chance to try Levain until now. I went to this location on a Saturday mid-afternoon and there was a line outside the door, but it moved pretty quickly since service was fast too.

I went with the chocolate chip walnut, two chip chocolate chip, and dark chocolate peanut butter cookies. I heated them back up in the oven and the cookies were delicious! So sweet, gooey and thick. The cookies are huge, so I personally think the price is worth it. I also got a slice of the sour cream coffee cake. It was sweet and good, but it didn't really taste like coffee- more like cinnamon.

Levain has already made its mark as making some of the best cookies. You can order online for delivery and you can even buy them from Whole Foods now. However, I think nothing beats getting them fresh from the stores. Highly recommend visiting if you're in NYC.","time":1651028978,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Micaela Moreno","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115491684697888728842/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TUa3GyrmhWHb0mOXq60VZk0v3vVevMTDSiAaLH=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"Had to try one of the most famous NY cookies and it lived up to my expectations! The place is small and cozy and the employees very kind. The smell you get as you enter is amazing and in sync with how appealing everything looks. I tried the Chocolate Chip Walnut Cookie and I loved that it was warm and crispy on the outside and chewy on the inside with the chocolate chips melting. Each cookie is 5 dollars.","time":1661870712,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Alee AR","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100724899210811505984/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QnJc949g4LDcjcfuy0qmUNzyB_xM6zdljzemUZNg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"I’ve always wanted to come try this bakery! This is my first time in NYC and this visit definitely was worthy! I encourage everyone to go to any location of levain bakeries you won’t be disappointed!

I had the chocolate chip walnut cookie, double chocolate peanut butter chip cookie, chocolate chip cookie and blueberry muffin.

The cookies were soft, warm and chewy in a perfect way. They’re sweet so you would just be able to eat a whole one or share pieces between your friends to try every flavor without getting cloying. Anyways we loved it, we shared two cookie flavors and tried the others at home. The blueberry muffin is at the perfect balance soft and not too sweet.","time":1656097316,"translated":false}]

column3: Hip spot serving coffee, pastries, baked eggs & other dishes in a low-key, comfortable space.
column8: 176 Ludlow St, New York, NY 10002, USA

column3: Chic rooms & suites in a refined hotel with a sophisticated restaurant & a stylish bar.
column8: 310 W Broadway, New York, NY 10013, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Romeo Vellutini","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108581222160017400687/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxYanDM33VcDxBY8xARiXpkGULtOxjstQ0wfLXWQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"The Grand is a very interesting hotel.  The rooms are small but very comfortable. Nicely furnished, great shower, and loved the electric wall heater which kept it warm and cozy in the bathroom. Nice bathrobes we supplied. The hotel has an old but modernized feel. One thing that was odd at first, but I grew to enjoy were the rather dark hallways. I don't think I ever heard anyone talking in the hallway, and it might be because of the dim light. All in all, it is very unique but great place to stay.","time":1668118733,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Rebecca Barnett","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108047674440268015186/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxZmdjetysPMVSztg56zAbYZJ7P0b9yt-9JyKsBg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"We stayed at the SOHO for two nights the week after Christmas, its a very nice boutique hotel and the location is great for shopping and restaurants. The valet and concierge service were both very welcoming we when arrived and while we were early for check in our luggage stored. We enjoyed a nice lunch in their bar/lounge area, shrimp cocktail and salads. The bar has a very nice selection of wine, cocktails and bourbons. The hotel was decorated very tastefully for the holidays. When our room was ready the front desk staff was very friendly and we were given a nice glass of champagne. Our room was a nice size, comfortable bed, x-large TV and a nice size bathroom with a walk in shower. There is also a nice selection of in room amenities (food/snacks/travel needs and personal items-just about anything you could need or want) that you can charge to your room. My only complaint is that later at night when we returned from our evenings (after 11:30pm) out there was a VERY strong smell of marijuana on the floor and it seemed to linger in our side of the floor, we did let the front desk know but the smell remained most of the night.
The bar has a fun late night vibe and you can order food well into the later hours, Wednesday night they have a nightclub that opens into the early morning hours. We had breakfast downstairs a their trendy 'diner' which was also good and another option for eating. We enjoyed our stay and would certainly come back again.","time":1672688224,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Skyler “Sky” Shuler","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111775636695107536322/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QRnDGhIMLyXmSNN4uwP4Eq-JjTt4YuHD2pE6oq=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"Salmon bagel and shrimp cocktail were delicious. The drinks were stellar also.

The bartender couldn’t make us our requested drink but we had so much fun tasting other things she could design!

Loved this experience.","time":1669733459,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Cassandra Clark","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111789063224741982353/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RVd5xVJbTQy6db6LnnEAq4jOCfZmcxqh9T8RnToQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"2 months ago","text":"Really friendly staff, nice rooms, comfy beds. Wasn't noisy at night even on a low floor which was pleasantly surprising.
Both the bar/restaurant and the diner had good food and service. Front desk provided complementary glass of prosecco at check in and was very nice. Overall a lovely hotel, and I'll def be back!","time":1675431102,"translated":false},{"author_name":"L V","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112496580541549440689/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Sp808fxlV7cjxDgr4L9T4pskvRD6RtyJeryQZaCw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":1,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"Looks nice and all but if you want to have sleep, better look for some any other place really. Asked for a quiet room and the put me right where all the outside noise is loudest- some time of machinery buzzing. Also, the AC/ air system failed to warm up the room. Woke up freezing and ended up sleeping no more than 4 hours due to all the above. Never again!","time":1669116186,"translated":false}]

column3: Established bakery supplying a range of traditional European-style breads & pastries.
column8: 88 Essex St, New York, NY 10002, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Patrice Kerremans","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106634938870828675601/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RQqQAYpaPq4hebOCmrMxneiWCFau_vl0h1oTs3Cg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":3,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"The staff is friendly and quick. All coffee is served way too hot and in disposable cups (whether you drink it inside or on-the-go). The cookies are too sweet. We got a loaf of Brioche Bread and one Ham & Cheese Croissant. It wasn’t the most valuable surprise bag we got from TooGoodToGo but it’s still a good deal. Their pastries were delicious, especially the croissant, which is crispy with flavorful filling.","time":1620334397,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Katy Cutright","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115002195921906157744/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5T0oMkQUTXnBCAq9KW5W-l3hu8cP-H1WDLb-tcqIg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"5 months ago","text":"Try the Black Forest Ham and Sea Salted Butter on a baguette. Keep up the great work y’all.","time":1678397538,"translated":false}]

column3: Small production, minimal intervention wines are the focus at this dimly lit haunt.
column8: 76 Orchard St, New York, NY 10002, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Cigdem Onat","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102769207217849271973/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TTOqU07w1--l4M0ZPsE_QBLjZo37NNh_GdfoCVvw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"Been here twice and both times were very pleasant. Good vibes good wines","time":1669088433,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Fouhmi","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108699048853975501873/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxZ9k2buE7bEtnCxL41SR9JryP77d085Wu35UHAd=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"A great place for a glass of natural wine. Staffs are friendly. The bar is on the smaller side, so prepared to wait on weekends. The bar is dark and romantic with exposed brick. But since it gets loud inside when it’s crowded, probably avoid on first dates?  Actually, forget about dates. Just go and   a beautiful bottle of white with friends.  BTG ranges from $14-20. They have a patio on sidewalk for those who prefer outdoor seating","time":1645735496,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Alba Aponte Muñoz","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104769069499333109811/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Q9-yuykpsh3PK5zwTDG-0jbx0Z1wZgzg4Ps5dL=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"Beautiful natural wine bar with the best vibes, 0 pretension, simple and delicious food to pair the wines with, knowledgeable staff, you can’t really get much more than this!!
A total must if you love natural wine with nice not stuffy energy.","time":1668439957,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Fei Li","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108250874236484393662/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Sw6KDTNMu77PD-O0C9OpudwA9Qw9E7ninQLP4I9w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Skin Contact is hands down my favorite wine bar in the city. They specialize in natural wines which really differentiates them from the crowd. Everyone, and especially Stefanie, is super welcoming, sweet, and knowledgeable about wines. No matter if you're a wine novice or connoisseur, the staff will be able to pick something that fits your palate.

We came on a Sunday and it was bustling but not full. There is bar counter, table, and outdoor seating. The ambiance would make for a great date or catch up spot. There were plenty of regulars which really attests to how great of a wine bar this is. They get pretty busy Friday and Saturday, so I would definitely come early or make a reservation on Resy!

Overall, would 100% recommend that you come check this place out before they become more well-known and hard to reserve! It's a wonderful local business and a great addition to LES.","time":1636947852,"translated":false},{"author_name":"LL","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101583238583153240412/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TM0OXhrq4FXcAQBha3zK3QUNZT-Eopk6WrShwerb4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":3,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Cute little spot with a good selection of natural/biodynamic wines, an intimate ambience, and helpful staff. They have both indoor and outdoor seating, indoor is cozy (not in a bad way), there’s also another room in the back; the outdoor seating is plentiful for such a small space. We had a short visit prior to dinner and didn’t dabble much into the food menu outside of pickles from “The Pickle Guys”. The wines we selected were 50/50: the Slovenian Malvasia was bright, complex, refreshing; the Australian Verdelho was overly bitter, pungent in a fermented kombucha way, and tasted tired—interesting enough to keep to see how it would open up as time progressed, wouldn’t order again. Ambience, selection, and staff are enough to warrant another visit.","time":1655390126,"translated":false}]

column3: Enduring Italian market offering housemade sausages & sauces plus meats, cheeses, oils & more.
column8: 260 Bleecker St, New York, NY 10014, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Gurleen","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109222121132207377373/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SyFZ4T6t_x6LeLrklSXplocHILLYGhCo6g1VQOTw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 weeks ago","text":"Literally the BEST sandwiches in NYC. They have been around since 1900 and know what they are doing. If you are in Manhattan you have to come here.

I also want to say that the staff here is AMAZING. They are super nice and fast! From the time you order your sandwich to the time they are done making it is maybe 3 mins total. That’s how fast they are. The sandwiches are huge and made with the freshest ingredients.

It’s a deli style so no place to sit and eat but perfect to take the sandwich on the go.

I highly recommend this spot.","time":1678903844,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Omar Arias","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113185209738494377848/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxbKMip9BwgIPB_cEZvHXHr3l-YcO_r0z4s03Q-Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"2 months ago","text":"Amazing! Got the Italian Special for $21 and fast service on a Saturday evening. They give you a huge portion that will last more than one sitting. I added mayo. You can also create your own combination that's not on the menu. Only thing I'd say is I have tasted a better (juicier) mozzarella and (sweeter) peppers from a Bronx Italian shop but those are just my taste buds, I like sweet and salty. I think $15 may be a more reasonable price based on size. The meats/cold cuts were excellent, I'll be returning.","time":1673760154,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Tay Jacobe","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116627511716443185942/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Thxok2XttS-BoJj0hVebZQ4HC17CQpVezk6cczWg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":3,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"Based on reviews, I expected to be blown away, but overall I was pretty disappointed. For $20 per sandwich, I’d expect a truly amazing experience but the only thing mind blowing was how BIG the sandwiches were. Otherwise, the flavors were pretty bland, although I appreciated that the meat and cheese and other garnishes were freshly sliced. I felt like maybe I was missing something - the sandwiches don’t have any sauce or anything, so there isn’t much flavor and it’s just unclear what the hype is all about.","time":1660278537,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Jessica Mark","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116099033372887003499/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5ROejWjBwSKK5k4C9IN0ALdHbbjBcZm2oy0pwJhOjg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Make sure to grab a ticket to get called up to order! Spending $15-$20+ on a hero may sound a bit pricey but this is FAICCO’S (and it can really serve two)! I highly recommend the chicken cutlet, with fresh mozzarella and pesto hero—add spicy peppers, trust me.","time":1657675754,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Mona Tong","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109221832895972766460/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TYVlGKb24RuxLo1wxniJTukeHMBKJ2SRxcG6tl1w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"Only got one item from here— the $1 Rice Balls—which I enjoyed! They came warm and toasted, and had a nice fried exterior with a super soft and mushy, delicate cheesy rice-filled interior. It was very flavorful and well-spiced, albeit a little too salty.

I didn’t try the expansive selection of heroes/sandwiches on the menu, but they seemed pretty expensive (~$19 on average), but they did sound delicious. Also just a note that credit cards have a 3% surcharge.","time":1669874013,"translated":false}]

column3: No-frills, cash-only burger counter hidden inside an upscale hotel.
column8: 119 W 56th St, New York, NY 10019, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"stan yu","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114879429039261666455/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QnZF4Rv66cmcBENYx2KONxmItFKX9ytjLOjobfTg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"Quite a hole in the wall burger joint and definitely a popular tourist spot. The burger with all the toppings “the wreck” was pretty good. It had a nice char to it and was juicy. I also ordered a side of cheese fries and I like that you get the option to have the cheese on the side or mixed in. I had it mixed in and the cheese was spread pretty evenly. However, the fries could use a bit more salt.

Overall, good food and fun decor but definitely on the pricier side.","time":1660965370,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Omar Arias","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113185209738494377848/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxbKMip9BwgIPB_cEZvHXHr3l-YcO_r0z4s03Q-Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"5 months ago","text":"My double bacon cheeseburger with sweet potato fries and oreo milk shake came out to $42+!! The food was good but I don't think anything is worth that price especially when its to-go style with some seating. You can find the place by going inside of the hotel and lining up by a red curtain past the lobby. Orders don't take that long but you'll have to stand around to wait for food. It seems like its become a popular destination for tourist and food lovers open to the high prices. When you're there be proactive and grab a table or ask staff to assist with getting the next available spot, its a free for all. It was an interesting experience, cool hidden vibe but a one time only experience.","time":1666917626,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Gui M.","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113749356771014725260/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Ttdhp9Q_BGyLunHzJOFAOkU_DC9rCbsLL-bDJciA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"The Burger Joint is a hidden burger place inside a Hyatt hotel. It exists within this narrow corridor, next to some red curtains. It is a very dream-like, Twin Peaks dream sort of hidden entrance. The bustling ambiance is its charm, with lots of little tables and high-tops for the customers to eat their food in a fast pace. The walls are covered with posters and black ink pen signatures and drawings. The place has a nighttime street fair vibe that is intoxicating.

As for the food, the cheeseburger with all the free toppings was good but nothing out of the ordinary, and the fries were not that good, but I would go back with a group of friends if I was ever in the area, given the fun vibe of the place.","time":1659121344,"translated":false},{"author_name":"다정","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116703739637651741797/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RX9-fS4VxoBxbEIyHk-BnSsVkTu5bIcliJlA62=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":3,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"Nice atmosphere but too tiny space. Barely find the space to dine in. It is little difficult to find the location of the restaurant. Taste of burger is good but the to go burger is wrapped with an A4 paper. I would rather choose eating Chick fill A... but it was nice to try them!","time":1660793695,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Chantal Hackett","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109032476819041757913/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RQ14KRFHqQvlZr4V7evWxgUOhFO0DY1sIsUwjS=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"11 months ago","text":"Truly a hidden gem! It is behind the lobby inside the hotel. Not easy to find but very much worth the hunt! Delicious hamburgers. Great fries. Good service when I took the fries back since they were not hot enough. No hassle. Polite and friendly staff. Cool music 😉","time":1650825598,"translated":false}]

column3: Cavelike, Paris-inspired jazz venue & cocktail bar under the Roxy Hotel, with regular live acts.
column8: 2 6th Avenue The Roxy Hotel, Cellar Level, New York, NY 10013, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Juan Marte","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100553464069690116928/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QkA5tSRLYgDeocE8G1_zUAixHIh9jsCT43xREy6g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"2 months ago","text":"It’s is a great surprise for those who love to enjoy some good jazz🎶. It’s better if you make a reservation, no wait time and help with the whole experience. There is a cover charge and a minimum to spend per person, so be ready to spend a little extra. Music was amazing, service excellent and the cheese board was fine. But, do not miss the experience and go with someone that would love and enjoy it!

Let me know how did it go after visiting 😊","time":1673924817,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Sofia De la Mora","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112725854344110217135/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QhFQVuuAIDBZCEC3WDshpfX3bMSKqNEBkvoka2NQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":3,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"Jazz club inside the Roxy Hotel. $25 cover plus 2 drinks minimum. Place and decor are amazing, gives a speakeasy vibe, sort of underground. The band that played was talented and has great vibes. Food and service were very disappointing- food was acceptable but took very long. “Cheese platter” was two pieces of goat cheese with a slab of jam. Had to ask the waiters several times to get anything which was frustrating. Whole group thought it was not worth it - expensive for a low quality experience. Will try to come back and give it another chance.","time":1662012810,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Hasanain Hasan","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112239997586915264755/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5T10eSLB20RR0E-iRHytXEumL_p1tksdz-_WZzi6A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"One of my favorite jazz venues in town. Went there twice.  Located at the basement of ROXY Hotel with chill early twentieth century vibes.
Super talented musicians, friendly staff and excellent service.
There s coverage, you need to book online, minimum two drinks apply. Little pricey and crowd are loud.
Bonus!!!! There s a retro cinema next door, where you can watch a movie before the jazz.","time":1664938181,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Hely Desai","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105970574428892920778/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxbBr1M8jqDpVeEdlSiMtEMLUCLvrP-p0_tmoE9y=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"I would give this place a 3 stars for service and actual experience but the was definitely worth the overall experience of going once. This was my first jazz show, and the performances were fantastic. The vibe of the speakeasy type club and the hotel are amazing.

It seems a bit of a “tourist trap” (unsurprising as it’s in a hotel) charging a cover and 2 drink minimum. They didn’t have any 3 of the bottles of wine we ordered but were able to recommend another bottle and gave us a good price on it for the inconvenience.

We ordered a cheese plate with a selection of cheeses chosen by the chef and found it funny that this simply meant 2 slices of brie, a cranberry slaw and 4 little pieces of toast. Not sure what “selection” was supposed to mean but I could make a better cheese plate from the dairy drawer in my fridge.

Overall, I’m glad I went once for the experience but likely would not go again.","time":1654448253,"translated":false},{"author_name":"William V","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106941016851690891002/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxb2h5cpcB5fGYhedIgaYUolFfzWGSN7AFw3cJPk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"A fantastic intimate jazz club. It is on the lower level of the Roxy hotel. This place is great. The food is good. The drinks are great, and the service is attentive and quick. Overall a great experience. There is a cover charge with two shows a night. It is a little pricey but I felt it was worth it. Pick the second show so you can stick around for more jazz. Reservations are a must.","time":1635265001,"translated":false}]

It was tasty and came with fries but it’s not a place to relax and enjoy the ambience. It’s in an out, very quick and expect to pay more than it says.","time":1666876335,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Julian MacKinnon","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105321413948628970357/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5T8Y6JfpgbLqkLBNaKDQacCyS5NSgn9JWJ9LKIL3g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a month ago","text":"This no frills old school diner transports you back in time to a 90’s era Seinfeld episode.
In some ways it’s a classic diner, in others it’s beautiful and unique. The food is all good, but the real charm lies in the simple details and the welcoming nature of the place.

I ordered the bacon and pancakes, and the cheeseburger deluxe. While the burger was good, the breakfast was special.","time":1676835679,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Chela","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108277407597432139648/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxbMXSpyi_8ue0Ejv_Gjxb3TIfprHnqClhaBDqxl=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"If you’re looking for an original “New York style” breakfast diner, look no further. Randomly stopped by for brunch and was taken aback by how charming and old school it was. There was one server, she was amazing. Very cheerful and quick as can be! The food came out quick and was just what I needed to continue walking in the cold winter city! If you’re in the area, don’t miss this place for a quick midday lunch/breakfast.","time":1639509449,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Karolina Celmanova","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111146408861506347688/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QIJjuXeY1NNg6lF0h5k2tdKyffspLtFOcucaxlYA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":2,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"sht was mid, pancakes were too salty and pastrami beef tough af. the fries were fried in old oil. the total on our ticket had a substantial service fee that we weren’t warned about. wouldnt recommend.😒","time":1659970693,"translated":false}]

column3: The Smithsonian's design collection & rotating exhibits are on display in this historic townhouse.
column8: 2 E 91st St, New York, NY 10128, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Benjamin Eschenbach","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114498799605333333202/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5R5nhWa4nSGh0-ccEvAEKvb0NABVjGtktpqLa1p=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"2 weeks ago","text":"If you're a design enthusiast, Cooper Hewitt in New York City is an absolute must-visit destination! This Smithsonian Design Museum, housed in the historic Andrew Carnegie Mansion, boasts a fantastic collection of innovative and thought-provoking exhibits that showcase the best in design, both past and present.

As I explored the various galleries, I was captivated by the diverse range of disciplines on display, including graphic design, textiles, industrial design, and more. The interactive exhibits were particularly engaging, inviting visitors to participate and experience design concepts firsthand.

The museum staff was friendly, approachable, and well-informed, ready to answer any questions and provide insights into the exhibits. I also appreciated the beautifully landscaped garden surrounding the mansion, which offered a peaceful retreat from the bustling city.

Cooper Hewitt is the perfect destination for anyone interested in design or simply looking for an inspiring and educational experience in New York City. I highly recommend paying a visit to this exceptional museum – you'll leave with a newfound appreciation for the world of design!","time":1679101037,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Michael Ion","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110653746722504184711/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QvJRvQn7Cl0KrRw16XCEbeEOdSQTIU2fx_Sfcgww=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"11 months ago","text":"There is a cafe here. You can grab coffee, latte or a snack and have a seat in their lovely picturesque garden. You will feel royal（笑）
You can also come here and photo bomb. Great place for pictures with fine scenery you can definitely catch some great snapshots or selfie's here.

Tip: the cafe is free to enter you don't need a ticket or anything just walk in through the garden entrance. If you want to observe the museum there is a ticket entry for that, which I did do as well but you can come here and enjoy the cafe and garden free to enter. They make very good coffee here and great snacks. Try it out. You'll want to become a regular.","time":1651343692,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Joey U","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101969426744162637479/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TCvRc-dipBgO03givSKYRZrGxFRGqbh1_P_PU7Vg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"5 months ago","text":"I came here for the National Design Week (we got free tickets) with a friend and it was a great time. The exhibits featured a variety of topics, from peace concepts, urbanism, to technology.

My favorite part about this museum is the ability to interact with some of the exhibits and take part in the creative process. My friend and I were a big fan of the Immersion Room, where you’re able to design your own pattern and project it onto the room. I found this to be a cool experience and a great creative outlet for me to explore. Do note that there is a bit of a wait if there are current groups ahead of you, and you only have 5 minutes to use the exhibit, which proved difficult for me and a few other visitors.

I like how this museum, despite its location on a historic villa, challenges the idea of the visitor as the explorer, and not just the viewer. Museums tend to have the visitor merely be the watcher of the exhibits, and not an active participant in the space. I feel this museum allows everyone of all backgrounds to get in touch with our creativity by literally having us use our senses to make something great.

Some of the docents were also very helpful and informative. I spoke with one docent who showed us the Designing for Peace exhibit and we explored conversations about how peaceful designs transcend into various environments. I appreciate how this exhibit expands the definition of “design” and does not limit it to the confines of “designing” textiles, furniture, etc. The biggest lesson learned here is that design is everywhere, and whether it’s obvious or not, there is a purpose to everything that surrounds us.","time":1666534594,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Megan Truong","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105893776533435491787/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5S4vudCCUrojReLYgC1XtFU-vqEdCPHNJaLQ3cihfc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"12 months ago","text":"A museum within itself, this place has so much history on its own. aside from the beautiful architecture and history behind this home-turned-museum, it has wonderfully relevant rotating exhibits, interactive screens scattered around, and a nice variety of fantastic permanent pieces. I love this museum, can’t wait to be back.","time":1649346663,"translated":false},{"author_name":"eva gartnerova","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104494589466754751720/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QQ-fDX3mYLLd8v45XxdAsfL8xv197FtlfTkwvILQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Great museum with lots of different exhibitions. They have so many great books about design in their shop.","time":1645311673,"translated":false}]

But, sometimes, a simple burger done right is the best. And here at 7th Street Burger, I felt like that is what they offer. Simple burgers done right. Therefore, no fancy menu, no add-ons, no substitutions. I like that about them.

The menu is: cheeseburger, Double Cheeseburger, and Impossible Burger. They also have Fries and some cold drinks, such as Mexican Coke. That is it. No need to take your think trying to decide what to order...

I believe they are made to order, since the order took about 5-10 minutes from when I placed the order. I love me some freshly made burgers and fries! The burger was super juicy, with nice thick pickles, and tasty sauce. Speaking of sauce, the dipping sauce that came with fries were great!

The staff was very friendly and polite, the interior was small but clean.
