Besides that, could come here again but only for a drink.","time":1660949993,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Michelle Pas","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102869276914301273710/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QpzPs0pWlL0EP4yV91sg3GA_WquzwiNuRloyVjgQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":1,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"I would give 0 stars if I could. Bartender was one of the rudest individuals I have ever come across in nyc. Don’t work in the service industry if you don’t like interacting with people!!!!

Came here for my BIRTHDAY as I live in the neighborhood and my bf ordered a soda water, which he charged him 2 dollars for. My bf pulls out his card and the bartender said there was a $15 minimum.

We asked if he would just accept the charge as we didn’t have cash. Daniel (I think the bartenders name) didn’t respond but grabbed the soda water out of my bfs hand and dumped it. He then grabbed the WATER out of my hand and dumped it.

Excuse me... WHAT? Who does that. I’m 28 years old and have never been treated like that, especially on my birthday!!

I then took a photo of him, which he freaked out about and kicked us out.

This guy in the stripped shirt should be fired, don’t work in service.","time":1628437637,"translated":false}]

column3: Simple pub grub, beer & cocktails are served in this classic old SoHo pub, dating back to 1847.
column8: 94 Prince St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Sabrina Moutarde","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101810856053493250350/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QhzP_fXJX7_gwNIuupMoM4G6_1rZBuUkkd8l7Y1xA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"We stumbled across this place whole shopping in Soho. Staff were great both friendly and efficient particularly the front of house lady. Service was good. I was recommended the Chilli soup. It was delicious!

We has an outside table/booth with heater. It was perfect for watching the world go by while  enjoying our lunch.

I wouldn't hesitate to go back.","time":1640947389,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Delow Red","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106487031771795420766/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxbd5_lQU66PyT4NtpcQlopbOeWOo_ppo67TvFQj=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"2 weeks ago","text":"Very nice place. Went here for breakfast. Ordered the omelette, around $16. Get to choose 3 options to put in it and side of fries. I got bacon, ham, and cheddar. Very well cooked and a lot of the toppings were on it. Service was quick and food came out quick too. Very friendly and nice. Would go back again and definitely worth the price.","time":1679252939,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Giovanni Porto","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106991710116576152772/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxbp0w8uIR6_sXj2gCYzHhZ0tvvf9t-zp4wi1OcJ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"2 months ago","text":"Fanelli cafe is a staple. I’m a born and raised New Yorker and have worked in the area as well as spent a lot of my youth in SoHo. Fanelli cafe is iconic and their bar food is great. The wings are crazy, the burger is straight to the point & exactly what you’d want from a bar burger and the staff is ILL. I came a lot during the pandemic and they were always in a chipper mood and happy to have us. I feel comfortable here, it feels familiar to a native New Yorker and one of the last places of its kind.  Not sure why I’ve NEVER written a review for them before, but I’m going tomorrow with the homies and I figured why not! Go here for that classic NYC American bar experience.","time":1673749504,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Muhamad Refky Kamajaya","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107206587485014259255/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QViOfwE1RnmYa9OBeutIwSc-ydaee9Cr8Zj49dxw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":2,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"While the portion was big, it was the worst burger I have ever eaten. The meat completely has no flavor. Service was swift and warm so I gave an extra star.

A friend ordered spaghetti and onion rings which they enjoyed.","time":1634016406,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Taylor Snipes","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115512093841003112505/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RovEHcyh37193eQanki2MHbaAVS8-iYJOE2oj6=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"This iconic cafe located in the heart of Soho is a perfect spot to grab a quick bite or pint and take a break from shopping. I love love love their onion rings. This things slap and are big. The burger is good too. If it’s a nice day out, be sure to grab a table outside for some great people watching. You might even spot a celeb!","time":1673017866,"translated":false}]

column3: Celebrated museum & library's gift shop featuring books, accessories & collection-related wares.
column8: 225 Madison Ave, New York, NY 10016, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Jessica Mark","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116099033372887003499/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5ROejWjBwSKK5k4C9IN0ALdHbbjBcZm2oy0pwJhOjg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Find the book room and be transported to a scene from Harry Potter. In this dimly-lit space, rare collection of literature and historical elements are on display. Upon exiting, be sure to look up at the domed ceiling covered with paintings comparable to the works in cathedrals in Italy. Take the glass-elevator to the upper levels for an aerial view of the main floor and cafe.

Currently on view are works by Rick Barton. Utilizing only pen and ink, Barton produced artwork that may appear underwhelming at first glance to some. However, it’s more fascinating viewing his work from the lens of his reality. The exhibit does not disappoint.

In another section of the museum on the upper floor, learn about JP Morgan and the design process of the Morgan Museum and Library building. Letters exchanged between Morgan and the architects, as well as floor plans, and structural designs and notes make you appreciate the surroundings that much more.

Also, be sure to visit the outdoor garden—modest yet enjoyable, especially on a pleasant day.

Reserve tickets in advance, and perhaps take advantage of Free Fridays is you can.

*Make note: this is not a lending library and compared to other museums in the city, the exhibits here are significantly smaller","time":1655857169,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Delaney Page","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102666265925818850148/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5ScG844cPe9tHc9MwaPWf1i9hk6gLovts7JWkor=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a week ago","text":"The building has a wealth of beauty in and of itself and the beautiful artifacts and art within serves to doubly amplify the collection housed here.  In the Morgan Library section there is absolutely no place the eyes can look without seeing additional details and artistic care.  Even the protective cases for the books have delicate flowers on them.
There was also a wonderfully bright atrium prior to the entrance into the library which serves as a wonderful place to rest, breathe, and relax with a drink.  On the day I visited a jazz band was also playing in the atrium which was a delightful addition.

I enjoyed exploring the library, the galleries, and generally the entire facility.  I would highly recommend it.

Additionally, they have free entrance after 5pm on Fridays.","time":1679730285,"translated":false},{"author_name":"David Richard","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101874445067003091779/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxZ0R75aXALQQU8z15WzYvIYOWpzAZUZ32JiFkEx=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Great spot!! While many would consider this a small museum I was pleasantly surprised at how much there was to view. I thoroughly enjoyed the beautiful historical library but there are also many additional exhibits/galleries full of great stuff. One can easily spend a full day here (4-5 hours). I was there on a weekday (Wednesday) and I really enjoyed the how peaceful and relaxed the overall atmosphere was.","time":1659731770,"translated":false},{"author_name":"ESB NYC","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115996293163942386176/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Qzyuw5ucsf0D1Cf0w10xuMTjV7ZzzdiIeu6rWn4L4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"This relatively small museum is one of Manhattan‘s gems. We went on the grand opening to celebrate the restoration of the small garden in front of the Museum’s original building. Pro tip: do not try too hard to coordinate your visit with the opening of the garden on Saturdays since it is very small and there is not really much to see. However, the museums interior has some beautiful galleries with curated exhibits in addition to JP Morgan’s personal collection of art and artifacts. There is a lovely gift shop with some interesting items for sale. There is also a nice café in the central indoor courtyard if you need a coffee or a snack. The new portions of the museum are on several levels and there is elevator service for your convenience.","time":1656278277,"translated":false},{"author_name":"J F","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102197601486599067086/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxbRMDpa_Tca8W6slLhYVyGmzKuI51zozuseZsBQAg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"11 months ago","text":"This is a fantastic museum, with a wonderful collections. The JP Morgan library was spectacular, as were the Holbein and Guthrie exhibits, both unique and special in their own right. What a treasure to have such a brilliant museum in the city, not too big and not too small. Completed our time there at a nice pace in 2 hrs.","time":1650041023,"translated":false}]

column3: Playful Mediterranean fare with Israeli influences & health-conscious ethos in a plant-filled space.
column8: 371 Broome St. &, 173 Mott St, New York, NY 10013, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Thomas Murtagh","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114073950420941983339/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxY5hZkrGH3MWWGZ_nXTaN59m8vzC4cr-hj2Pun9=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"Too good can’t even begin to describe it. The second you order a drink or food you blink and it was in front of you but in a good way. We had the hummus to start which was phenomenal. The pita bread was perfect and had “unlimited” refills which was great with the hummus. The shoo shoo cocktail was great for the both of us. I got the chicken schwarma which was incredibly tender and perfectly seasoned. Overall the this place was perfect between the service and overall environment.","time":1661652594,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Jason Guo","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111608069981087720937/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RHVq26ve9OZ-JucVa6OsoTTGZETISwKGPOkcxKETs=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"2 weeks ago","text":"A great brunch spot in Nolita. We had seats in their outside cabins which fit up to 8 people. The staff was very friendly and attentive. Almost all of us ordered the chicken schnitzel sandwich which was one of the best fried chicken sandwiches I’ve had. The Israeli pickles with the sesame crusted chicken and zhugg was incredible. It also comes with fries that are nice and crispy.

Some folks also got the harissa burger which was tender and juicy!","time":1679531423,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Nadia G R","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115340780850447765538/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxaZx059Pyxjj-mkPyoy5Bxh64M6aR-PkA-Bte5b=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"5 months ago","text":"I absolutely loved dinner at Shoo Shoo. Everything was so fresh and flavorful and the service was great and friendly. Nicely laid out, clean restaurant, did not feel crowded at all and they have a huge outdoor eating space as well. For starters, shared the hummus and baba ganoush with pita. For my main meal, I had the octopus from the starter menu and a side of roasted cauliflower. All of the dishes blew me away. Would definitely return!","time":1666981207,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Chris S.","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116227901818348307497/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxbXA4BneYVYBUPJiuo7IK_V970Y4jYPb-l4Ii0f=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"I’ve been to Shoo Shoo multiple times and each time the food and service is amazing. Hummus for the table is a must but I most recently had the cod shawarma and it was so good. The outside seating options are abundant but I personally love the atmosphere inside.","time":1654349468,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ankita Nayak","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115140308509125174314/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxa-qE5S8FE3nWkp-jAhhGK-kVIp-zlnpbeRaLulfhU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"2 months ago","text":"I came to shoo shoo to celebrate my birthday! They have these cute outdoor booths that seat up to 8 and are heated. It worked out perfectly for my group.

We shared a lot of plates and I have a few pictured below - Japanese eggplant, lamb arayes and shoo shoo kebab, all of the food was DELICIOUS and the service staff was also wonderful - constantly checking up on us!

the drinks are also phenomenal, only thing is the shareables are more for 2-3 people, if you have a big group, I suggest getting individual entrees for everyone.","time":1674237170,"translated":false}]

column3: Bustling destination with chef's tables turning out kebabs & seafood specialties.
column8: 230 9th Ave, New York, NY 10001, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Rashmi Ambewadikar","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103899268373798009829/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxasZVGGQawUpeJWHG9NE2HP3jpcsCUYtsqA1Vl2=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"I had a great meal at Shukette last night.  I dined solo and enjoyed sitting at the chef’s counter watching the chefs skillfully and artfully prepare all of the dishes.  All of the small plates I had were delicious.  The tahini soft serve at the end was delightful- even if you’re stuffed from everything you ate, don’t skip it.  The place has a great vibe. The service was efficient, attentive, and friendly.  The manager greeted me at the end of the meal to make sure everything went well.  I will definitely be returning!","time":1653143799,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Tyler Colburn","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116770943341194844369/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxYfkxwNsy734I2go35sHP7x8V1pcgi6LclNteoc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":3,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"The pickled vegetables are very good! The fried artichokes are not that great. The only flavor we could taste was the oil they were fried in. The grilled nectarine and cheese was a good idea, but the nectarine wasn’t sweet or ripe. The breads (all of them) that we ordered were amazing! Would eat them all over again. The fish salad and bean dip were both decent, but nothing really notable with either of those dishes. The calamari surprisingly wasn’t very flavorful, but the steak was delicious.

Overall, the restaurant was not very impressive, except for the pickled veggies and breads. Not sure what all the hype is about. You can get much better Middle Eastern food at a better price at several other places in the city.","time":1660368052,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Erdwing Nieto","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108423859408116798073/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QgUzCcXo_1YZOk4S4LQ9BzRscm85fkFBWLFxlzyw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"What an incredible experience we had. The place was crowded but it still felt really nice and that everyone had their own space. Our server (His name is Angel) was absolutely helpful and very insightful about the menu, he pretty much ordered everything we had and i can say it was a great decision.

The quality and flavor of everything we had was really fresh, and very specific flavors that made all the menu taste so interesting. We tried almost all the dips, they were amazing and also the Moroccan bread, and Pita were absolutely lovely with the dips. Then we moved to the Wrapped cricket feta, The steak kebab and The lamb skewer.

We finished with a really interesting dessert, the only on the menu: Tahini Soft Serve","time":1642301559,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Jacqueline Cerniglia Dion","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109018901222193933826/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5T5LFGFN-VeaL_0RIA1e5QaOS5BheYqquk-BZUKe7s=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"11 months ago","text":"Immediate favorite. Had awesome chef counter seats down at the end of counter towards back so could see every plated meal and got complimentary dishes from the kindest chef on the line. Staff was super helpful in guiding our choices. There was more we wanted to order - so coming with a group of four would be even better so could try more. Favorites were the dip with apricots, the new fava bean dip, crispy artichoke with amazing lemon flavor. Don’t skip on the chicken or the ice cream… even when we couldn’t finish it because we were so full was def worth the few bites.","time":1652095490,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Logan Porter","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104635840534298014803/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Rds8RwPCgeZ16J8q1ZP4br_WKaQHA-Eso1G-k_sA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"If you’re looking for a place to try a whole bunch of stuff after a long workday - this is the spot for you. Incredible bites that will leave you full and happy. The Frena was so good we ordered an additional piece - don’t go here and not get a piece! Something about soft garlic on a fresh piece of bread is just the icing on the cake.

Note: if you’re looking to drink they have a long list of wines but a pretty small list of cocktails. Perfect for someone who wants a glass with bites!","time":1659493054,"translated":false}]

column3: undefined
column8: 101 Spring St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11: [{"author_name":"Annabelle","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111731769581686999661/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxZhFqCFnKu7yhU0Uh2RLm6ylA2wM5TaueWZB6_O=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":1,"relative_time_description":"a month ago","text":"Visited the foundation last Saturday on Feb 11th 2023. The foundation itself is absolutely spectacular of course however the horrific tour guide ruined it. Not only did she have no passion at all for art and Judd, but wasn't able to provide any insight beyond stating the obvious. All questions were answered by superficial answers. For example, I want to know what's the link between Chamberlain's piece in the bedroom and Judd for instance? Why did Judd move to Marfa to find solitude when in NYC he was apparently all about entertaining? What's the context of Flavin gifting him an installation etc? I would summarize the tour guide as rude, uptight, no passion and a clear language barrier.","time":1676488267,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Xavi Menós","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115704047186202994553/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5REnz7QSJphxHAUI658HxWTZTQlMq-gzb2W-gDZJg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2","rating":3,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"An incredible space (a five story building in Soho) that helps you understand the work and life of Donald Judd. The problem: the lack of a proper explanation by Judd’s on-site guide. If you don’t know who Judd was or what he stood for, you will end up the visit without knowing anything about him (unless someone on your group has asked). My piece of advice: do your homework before visiting the foundation, if not you will end up properly confused by the lack of motivation and explanation of the guide.","time":1634429490,"translated":false},{"author_name":"David Clark-Bell","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112558108853411523469/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QAdxJuxNYgS_qzz-GxhSe6BaSXINRr1mBq6AfOqn4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"5 years ago","text":"I visited the Donald Judd exhibit about 2 years ago and had a wonderful tour. The guides were very informative and interesting to hear the stories about how Judd worked. I loved looking at the Dan Flaven's work on the top floor. This building was so important to Donald Judd's use of proportions that it is a significant insight into how he created his work. If you like Donald Judd this is a must-do visit, enjoy!","time":1521899258,"translated":false},{"author_name":"JJ Acuna","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100978397890477753775/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Q_jna63fDcCYE-eth8K-tOpaMrMsLof7FlUX4eIl4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 years ago","text":"Really amazing opportunity to see the private workshop, home, and living space of the are great artist, Donald Judd. You can't just show up, all reservations for tour are made online with a 3 month wait. It's definitely worth it though. Really a joy to see a home like this.","time":1402242371,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Majdi Alkarute","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112487271570925280595/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TxwU6SMInaY8rKb23jq8yeweiTsONP0V1saSEbfw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 years ago","text":"Register online and Talented staff will give you a small group tour of the building. Incredible architecture, furniture, and art inside by multiple well known artists ! Well worth the price.","time":1562549179,"translated":false}]

column3: Italian place by the Charlie Bird team for wood-fired pies, meats and fish from the open kitchen.
column8: 187 Mulberry St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Peter J. Irwin","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104990218198725771350/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxazqE4rFlkq_ZM0pi3UcDpFq2wHxgWAdiFbjLsm=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"11 months ago","text":"Wow, I don't know where to start. I know, how about the bread? For a party of 5, they gave us 2 pieces of bread. The pizza crust didn't taste good. I had the bucatini and while it tasted good, they gave me the smallest portion ever. I can't believe I paid $26 for that. For the first time ever in an Italian restaurant, I left hungry and I'm not a big eater. They usually get good reviews, so maybe we just went on an off day, but none of us enjoyed our meal. I was beyond disappointed and don't know if I'll ever try them again.

The food is phenomenal. We stopped here on our cross-country trip. I'm just loving it, I would love to come again.","time":1651877493,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Zarina","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103696902495547969115/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QlW6suvM4Qx16HJeHSkyZI9OS-Q9x1D4BGNyPqOg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":3,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Environment was nice & open.  Great ambiance and energy.  Staff were curteous and attentive. One co ed bathroom on the main floor (another downstairs). The food was average. Very small portions for an Italian restaurant. column11:
[{"author_name":"Irma Zandl","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101579716857027286357/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5R47GTeT_iAcqobkTF1jN1VAKNnjlEdRVScT3WvK0Y=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"This place is a total gem. LOVE it and  would rank it 5 stars for ambiance, vibe, crowd, cocktails. The vegan food doesn't do it for me, and would probably drop it to a 3 (but remember I'm not a vegan so not really fair to judge). The vegan friends I was with, love it!","time":1657974034,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Caroline Dudley","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100244470329572116830/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5T9X-M92Hfc9P4RBr8icUI-rYPmKFymDZev22PFSg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"Public Records, you are a haven for true music lovers and music explorers.  I love what you stand for, the community you nurture, and how thoughtfully and cleverly you integrate artists with the space. The menu was short and sweet but delivered strongly from the new head chef (congrats Tanea Cash!). The drinks menu impressed as well.  Not only all this, but the indoor and outdoor spaces are well maintained and the service, wonderful! And to top it all off, Public Records IS the vibe because every single patron I encountered was polite and courteous. This is such a respectful yet fun and artistic environment! The price of some of the cocktails are a bit steep but the complete experience matched by the energy of the Public Records goers was well worth it.  I assume this is all thanks to incredible management, so thank you 🙏","time":1668639232,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Sarah G P","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114386416141721286565/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QUa_42I4DUkH3gt5HRlEElWN30K-eZJtU2nMDXng=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Everything was absolutely delicious. column11:
[{"author_name":"Hannah Ponce","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100021952922422123527/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SIe6I6wF-CLgEjiWjzfKGd6B44dZpHE05PhdpXMg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"A West village must visit! The yogurt granola + chai latte are my absolute personal favorite. Their wine selection is phenomenal. I make sure I visit this spot every time I’m in NY. Their staff is always attentive and helpful. This cozy, effortless, characteristic  spot is one you can’t miss for any time.

Truly a great change + addition to the west village.","time":1662092006,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Jamie Geddes","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103333890649987476812/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QnSQ8K--Il0Q3a6b6K9IgK7cdKyRCRgesFc0cTuw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"St. Jardim is perfect. The menu from day to night is super impressive as well – I'm obsessed with the Vegetable Toast. column3: Stylish restaurant serving contemporary cuisine in an intimate, informal setting.
column8: 47 E Houston St 1st floor, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Natalie Young","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110487257002680179879/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RJTHWYw0c_QGukFj3IohDL6UuuNYNuPyUCvmTHRA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":3,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"I was a bit disappointed with the experience at Estela - a place I had heard great things about.

The cuisine is not cohesive in any way, from what I could tell… a bit too “New American” perhaps. The dishes are meant to be shared; however, each small dish costs anywhere from approximately $20-$40. They recommend you order around 7 items for a group of four. Granted there are only about 12 items on this particular brunch/lunch menu, so it almost seemed as if we needed to order one of each dish to be full.

I do not recommend the crab dish, I forgot to take a photograph of it because I was deterred by the sight of it. It was very very fishy to taste, you could even smell it.

The best dish was the mushroom dumplings and the arroz with squid. However, for the tiny portion sizes and the cost, I am not sure if the flavor was that impressive.

The chicken entree was so strange. Two small pieces of chicken that tasted so regular. Some orange type of purée and squash.

The restaurant itself was cute- small and quaint. The service was good, normal - not above and beyond or anything memorable.

Perhaps the dinner would be a better option for people who have booked reservations far in advance and are looking forward to the meal because unfortunately I was not very satisfied with the brunch / lunch experience.","time":1669141717,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Karsen Yack","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111481227809925576172/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5R8GCYSwv_9u07Lm0mvLhnHlkB7nzM4fgsmqRmW5Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"5 months ago","text":"Food was really really good, and I love how it’s so unassuming, but intimate. Only have positives to say, but my one negative is  I felt the service was just a little slow. One of those experiences where your drinks sit empty for four or five minutes too long and you start to wonder where your food is. Nothing too crazy or unbearable, but I think a slightly quicker service would be beneficial!","time":1666462771,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Claire-Elizabeth Diamond","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115742494807562191130/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxaDAD8ij5RdI_FE1ArDzipb2fRkp4SUg7PDi5MR=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"2 months ago","text":"One of the best dining experiences I’ve had in NYC. The staff were all lovely and attentive, especially our server Gavin who was an absolute dream. We had the scallop, fried arroz and the ricotta dumplings. Just perfection.","time":1675641006,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Bruno Rigonatti Mendes","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111679721214298065154/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RaMuWKUD2Ov-6i_hsJ12gUQH3cD6eI59U4mSGILYc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Estela has all that downtown New York charm you’d expect of a dim, cozy and loud first floor restaurant. The endive salad is iconic and worth the visit alone. We also enjoyed the jamon, ricotta dumplings and duck we ordered. But the endives were on a different level! Four dishes were enough for two. Drinks aren’t cheap, but they sure are strong! (That’s a compliment.)","time":1659850469,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Murilo","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107410004822495876118/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TIw8v4eg_vure3poVkLfrWuzfL2UOU6dPcF9V2v-8=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"Amazing food experience. Tuna and beef tartare are a must. The ricotta dumplings was mind blowing and the duck was so rich in flavors that we didn't want it to end. Skip the pork and try not to eat too much bread (hard, given the bread is perfect).
Service at the bar was 5 stars; at the table was a bit pretentious (poor attention, didn't helped much)","time":1660176473,"translated":false}]

column3: Blackboard specials supplement the small menu at this Italian spot known for its glamorous crowd.
column8: 268 6th Ave, New York, NY 10014, USA
column11: [{"author_name":"Eric San José","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100332114238682402189/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RrcJyMKejt-QpKpOPrNKbkPpBvKLfxBX2GGfr7ig=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba8","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"11 months ago","text":"Arrived at 4:30pm on a Monday for an early dinner.   Was seated right away.   Outdoor seating is available.   Moderately clean facilities.   Specials are written in Italian and my server had a problem translating it into English for me, but we figured it out.   He didn't read the entire menu to me,  just a few selected items.   The olive oil for the bread was quite bitter.  The meatball Appetizer was a little bland.   Black truffle pasta was very good.   Papardelle pasta was the Star 🌟.   Veal medallions were very good too.    Our 2 Servers were having an argument in the dining room which was witnessed by the other patrons.   Quite expensive for a casual place.   CASH ONLY.   I'm giving a cautious 4 Stars because the food was good.   But I noticed many bad reviews here for service,  prices,  and portion size.","time":1649774398,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Dani Levin","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112211287874036344557/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5ScpRnD6xkmLw-XqaH-abhesurLhy-ocQysGktwvA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"Was super delicious, good vibe. The desert was almost better than the pasta. We sat outside, it was great time and would def recommend. Cash only so be prepared and expensive so should have a good amount.","time":1660949512,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Anastasia Yules","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100997139983679591567/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Q6tB17hopanWb-STkDtegG2ZdEUt0wckPnvOLL-A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"I was planning to visit another Italian restaurant around the neighbourhood, but it was closed. So I went to Bar Pitti only to realised that my favourite actress went there and Bar Pitti has been saved on my maps. I was greeted by a very friendly staff and I was handed a small board of menu. I'm not a big pasta fan, but on that day I really felt like getting some pasta. I ended up choosing Pappardelle, their classic menu (apparently so famous that people are trying to replicate it). The portion wasn't as big, but it was some beautifully cooked pasta. While flavourful, as a meat lover I found the meat to be almost non-existent and I wasn't too happy about that. For a portion of pasta + tax + tip I spent about $28. It was definitely one of the most expensive pasta I've ever eaten.","time":1643500529,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Olena Perez","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102912463599901127046/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxa1LIa9gUt8R6-wLLBQf00PjMZaTuys2vQph9B4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Walked in without res & seated immediately. Great vibe. Loved the truffle pasta and the lobster ravioli. Desserts were fabulous. Had a very nice experience here!","time":1655808398,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Natasha Saleh","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104934508453314434658/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TMkjX35dkbPKFqq-8kxZgQgvKk1q0MaqjaKcSTFVQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"Loved the fried mushrooms, and eggplant parmigiana appetizer. The chickpea purée soup was phenomenal. The spaghetti was a bit too Al dente for me but the meatball was good. The service is amazing","time":1668782103,"translated":false}]

column3: High-end takes on red-sauce fare await at this A-lister Italian restaurant in a retro-glam space.
column8: 181 Thompson St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Isabel Castro","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107670123705613145626/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SWQFv3vxTuPp10AIc2IfZG8h8EYVoTa6f9ZkHsTQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"Honestly, the best part was the “free” appetizer of garlic bread, anti pasta and FRESH MOZZARELLA. I was speechless, it was delicious and a great way to start the experience at this restaurant. Inside is really nice, had an elegant vibe and the China sets on the table are very unique. The servers are so nice and helped my group pick certain things off the menu. The food did take some time to come out but this isn’t fast food, this was all done to order, you could TASTE is. The presentation and taste was worth the wait. My group of three ordered a Caesar salad to share, spicy rigatoni and the veal Parmesan. This place definitely met the hype it receives but I took off one star because it’s difficult to get a reservation and it’s definitely on the higher end of price. Again, just my opinion. I would come back here 100% for a special occasion or for when you want to feel like a superstar :) I highly recommend coming here at least once to experience it because this lovely gem was a complete experience I will never forget!!!!!","time":1654735652,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Srida Saraogi","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100456094793011851311/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Tec-MwwqqfsHnFBQVo2J5bzJV7afc3je7gyD9pGf8=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":3,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Honestly very average pasta. You could make it at home for 1/10 the price. We got the special (truffle fettuccine) and it was $75  and it was not that great. The spicy rigatoni was better, but again could be made at home . The carrot cake was a bit dry. The frosting and ice cream that came with it were good.","time":1642969612,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Taylor Snipes","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115512093841003112505/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RovEHcyh37193eQanki2MHbaAVS8-iYJOE2oj6=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"It’s worth the hype! IF you can manage to get a reservation, DO IT! The (very) spicy rigatoni is a staple and a must try. My favorite was the veal parmigiana - chefs kiss! I love the vibe in this place. It feels like you’re in a scene from The Godfather. Be careful about the bread they bring out at first. It’s so good and easy to fill up on. Get the Caesar! One of the best I’ve ever had. Oh and the meatballs may not be on the menu but they are a must try.","time":1652471394,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ryan Rike","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109004681353561104173/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RyPiYOInQzmW4t_yXDSUIKBbSq2chUTMY3AGVTTh4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Best meal I've had in my life. The service was outstanding. I got the spicy rigatoni and meatballs and couldn't believe how delicious it was. The rigatoni wasn't too spicy but had a nice kick. For dessert I had the carrot cake and ginger ice-cream.

I really enjoyed sitting out in the patio out front of the restaurant, great space.

Can't wait to go back next time I come to New York!","time":1657657339,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Melissa Donato","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109385491555741774093/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5R8PJyQoeV7y4U6jlOF1M7u2E0k-Y0aO65aVyWgXBU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Food was delicious and service was super friendly. I would’ve given five stars, but there were a few things that disappointed me.

1) Be careful what you order. I ordered a lasagna thinking that it would be a single piece. I was not warned that ordering lasagna means ordering an ENTIRE tray that costs a crazy amount of money. That feels like something you should clarify with your guests?

2) I felt very rushed. Plates were taken away with food still on them. The check came before it was even asked for. It felt like they were trying to turn tables very quickly.

Overall it was a good experience, but could’ve been better.","time":1640881271,"translated":false}]

column3: Classic New York-style bagels offered with an array of spreads & smoked fish & an all-day deli menu.
column8: 500 6th Ave, New York, NY 10011, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"John Pozo","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107712351726952430758/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5T6j8LHLIycIC6CqI1ZVA0cPsazfHWlum0mTyIJ-PU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"5 months ago","text":"Fast and friendly service.

I stopped in the morning on the weekday and luckily had not wait issues as some reviews pointed out but those were for the weekend. So take this with a grain of salt if you decide to check them out on the weekend.

The bagel was a pretty good not sure what qualifies as a New York Bagel but it was definitely good.

Coffee was ok Id say get a bagel or sandwich and grab coffee from another spot.","time":1667409545,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Monika Rosa","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105873818655623270479/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5R853fkCe32gHk7DoPW7wBsvzIN9Q25i6HTyURZSw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a month ago","text":"Bagels were very tasty - “Two Scrambled Eggs on a Bagel” (Breakfast Sandwiches offer) with additional cheddar and “Maple Raisin Walnut Cream Cheese Sandwich” with some additional spicy pumpkin spread (Spread Sandwiches offer). Pumpkin flavour was super good. The queue was reasonable, the place clean and we easily found a free spot to sit and eat inside.","time":1676835103,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Rob Robinson","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104125553877532798417/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SF7e_fgcsTk-G_8ybV0O-Ie4Uc7YvGX6cTASDZsO0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Friendly staff and tasty bagels! We've had a few bagels from here now and they're always fresh and generously filled. If you're struggling with choice, then you won't go wrong with The Traditional (salmon and cream cheese with onions and capers). I had this one on a whole wheat Rainbow bagel over the Pride weekend and it was perfect. Good drink selection and efficient service!","time":1656428458,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Katherine Poole (Katie)","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106627114327565032087/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SAj41VnB-26e_CkP7XRFnpmTxDu_Tri8LKdWZ4l10=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"11 months ago","text":"Delicious! It was our first visit and it was busy (always a good sign) so was a bit tricky to figure out our order. But the staff were lovely and we lucked out with a seat inside by the window. Well worth it.","time":1649884804,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Eva Lakirovich","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111485274378766129608/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QEtH2Lh22_oHf7PPv1wjUCzaR9gQvSF7sKZselFQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"This is my favorite and most loved bagel shop in NYC! Look no further for perfect bagels! I love their egg and cheese bagel and my favorite is the traditional smoked salmon! It’s so fresh and the combination of flavors are perfect! On the weekend it’s quite the wait but definitely worth it! Thanks Murray’s for making my weekend in NYC with the perfect bagels!","time":1649033457,"translated":false}]

column3: Handmade Chinese dumplings, soups & sesame pancakes in a snug counter-serve with a street-art mural.
column8: 74 Hester St, New York, NY 10002, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Nathaniel Downes","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113196825881884185589/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QhdD0VluXU0zlPO3wYbzvOn72waMOEJWQR6cTC0g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"11 months ago","text":"The dumplings here are extremely good for the price. Servings are so cheap and i was able to buy over 30 dumplings for under 10 dollars.

I recommend above all else the pan fried dumplings, but the boiled dumplings (get the soup too!) are also very good. I also loved the sesame pancake, but make sure to get a filling otherwise it’s a huge piece of bread.

You literally cannot beat the deals here and if i lived nearby it would be over for my health and wallet. Cash only!!!","time":1652158104,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Juan Lima","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105662480087228726221/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxZpb_fru68KvRscJxvSbUtnNioog8UDLxeMNchw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"This is a very decent place to get fried dumplings and fried buns for a very competitive price! 10 chive and pork dumplings, 4 fried buns with a beverage for under 10 bucks. The dumplings had a nice golden brown crust on the bottom, a bit crunchy and juicy when you eat it while it is still hot. The fried pork buns were so hot they were steaming the plastic container it came in. A bit of soy sauce and hot sauce (if it was available) would have made for a perfect combination. There are many other items available and these two are #1 and #2 respectively on their menu. These are their best sellers so they are must try items if you decide to grab a bite.","time":1648169415,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Christina Ng","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107673254960936430246/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SSy4jdWmNb4rj3eEIjl8VWx83jUBkiOfvOtwyqSw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"Cash only! But that’s fine if you are prepared.  As always don’t look in a Chinese kitchen or the floor etc.  For 2 of us it was a bit too much food but wanted to try things. Can’t believe all this food was under $20!  10 pork and chive dumplings are only $3.50. I could use a larger sauce cup but maybe that is just for to go sauce. The dumplings are too big to dip so I just put it on the plate.

Chive and pork dumping on plate great with the sauce on the table

Beef stew noodle soup good and big for the price

Hot and sour soup

Fried pork buns - good not as doughy or heavy as other places

Coke","time":1672957686,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Adrian","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101439553833354026450/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxYBwssf8GO7Ll2HVwjyaydDYKtp5v7_T9bifgMC=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"11 months ago","text":"If you’re a LES dumpling historian like me then you know your history. The man behind the counter is the same person from Prosperity dumplings that’s now permanently closed. They by far had the best dumplings and the cheapest at 4 for $1. I asked the man if he remember me as I haven’t seen him since 2016 and he said he did, I’m glad to see their business thriving once again as we always told him he needed a bigger store for the demand ! I recommend the sesame pancake or the sesame pancake with duck","time":1650032568,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Michael Helmlinger","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102575928766161358290/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RlBSuwj8N5XtjAoopm-A1YUjt3AXDYiV3hFh9s=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"Based on some YouTube recommendations we took a quick bite around lunch. Paid 5$ for Shrimp and Pork dumplings on a plate. Worth every penny. Food was very delicious. Owner is little bit hard to understand for foreigners but very friendly. Recommend this place :)","time":1662381802,"translated":false}]

column3: Funky taverna lures locals with drinks & simple American-Mediterranean dishes for brunch & dinner.
column8: 138 Division St, New York, NY 10002, USA
column11: [{"author_name":"Jana Iris","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110983707223151735812/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SoOgD8qwxTlB-cZn3Kf6uMnJ9Wmrkg2p3md34AfQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Amazing neighborhood spot. I walked by this place a bunch until I finally ate there. Service was amazing. Food was delicious. Not pretentious at all. Felt very authentic. I’m definitely planning on becoming a regular here.","time":1658875028,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Franjez","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112464858785745680405/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QGMXlJQc3XQ8d_qwGa6QFYLdBioncZiW1Q7c3jMQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"GEM! A quiet dive bar with amazing food & cocktails. Outdoor seating. Attentive & friendly staff.","time":1655213391,"translated":false},{"author_name":"CLARE KELLY","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107535154587390923975/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Tfld-7ryaPOtANqpY0lRfH9SkH8voqunps7xgVxw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Went here with a group of friends and the staff, food, and atmosphere were 👨‍🍳💋👌. I got the spicy watermelon margarita, I HIGHLY recommend this, probably one of my fav drinks I've had in NYC. If you are looking for a chill environment that feels like a true NYC bar, this is your place. I had a great time here.","time":1658425429,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Eric Finkelstein","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111444671146808251214/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxZj3UXlgWeTULryVeYQ15zwvpuoFHhgdKEcNQIf=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba8","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Hootsla: Delicious French toast bites. Huge quantity.\nBuffalo wings: Very crispy. While I've never had strong feelings about Buffalo wings, a more opinionated acquaintance called them the best in NYC, and I can see that.","time":1636948607,"translated":false},{"author_name":"John van Bockxmeer","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109571522102167541627/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TRr87cCLSPsDR9vVGSjfA49ariFyrW26xynU0yfNU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"5 months ago","text":"This place is great, can recommend. Very chill vibes and excellent comfort food. The chickpea coconut stew was delicious with crunchy onion pieces ontop. Staff are speedy and the prices are still very reasonable. You can even play board games and sit to relax also. Doesn't feel rushed at all.","time":1665351868,"translated":false}]

column3: Longtime East Village eatery showcasing classic French bistro cooking in a Parisian-style room.
column8: 14 1st Ave., New York, NY 10009, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Hannah French","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102169361876934665246/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SLD8jPOXiGmTVgu1nJgGXolC7X8OP93jGCVNOPxAg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"This restaurant is truly a warm and cozy experience. I did make reservations and would recommend them because it was very busy! The table was small and you sit close to people but I think that sometimes is a really nice vibe. I think the lighting and pictures on the wall made the place feel very homey yet classy. The french I sprinted menu is good for people who don’t know what they want. I tried the steak, mashed potatoes, french onion soup, escargots, chicken, and white wine. All of which was so yummy and truly worth the price. The french onion soup is a must ! I also started the night with an espresso martini and it was strong and made perfect. I think this is a great spot to get dressed up and even get drinks- there is a bar. Also a great choice for a birthday dinner ( which is what I was there for)","time":1670290470,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Kristina I","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110501002456997935208/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TAlHMPlvVKbmckX3qXHf_G9WZnhhE6J4hfbmOpKw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"I had been wanting to try Lucien for a long time, and so when my sister was visiting it felt like a perfect opportunity to try it out!! Seafood was delicious & fresh — the grilled octopus amazing. Be prepared to spend upwards of $20 for a simple salad (arugula, parm cheese and fennel) and $17 for a soup. Pricey, but worth it.","time":1661598461,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ray Morales","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106371971095475977887/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5T9-SW9QxU3DcpvtoEwVhs2FxKjufuJT6djtM9PTQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"This place has a vibe that’s so rich and cozy, the experience was really great being here. The drinks was tasty and the food was delicious. Had the steak frites and was not disappointed at all. My only thing is about this place is because the atmosphere is so great and welcoming, it can get very very crowded, especially if a celebrity or two is there or drops by. So make sure you’re there early or on an off peak day.","time":1671218981,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Olivia Hopkins","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104365523950393168632/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxZ7b-puel6RDsBSeR2gtd2tlM5CBjHcvHU2lGzK=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"Definitely worth a visit! We had the onion soup and the escargots (snails) for starters, which were very good. The highlight was the scallops with mashed potatoes, which was exceptional.","time":1664946703,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Brett East","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100604927999107150066/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SyfVOWelwsZXct792Z4nM1mKEctHu2gtYuxXP49G0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"12 months ago","text":"I was told that this place is very scene-y, so I was skeptical of the food. And while it is definitely scene-y - I've never seen so many pairs go in and out of a single stall bathroom on a Thursday at 7pm - the food is really good and worth the visit on its own.
Usually I avoid fillet mignon in favour of meatier cuts, but the steak au poivre is delicious and reminded me of how good a lean, tender steak could be - highly recommend.
I'd suggest making a res, the day we tried to walk-in, they were booked for the evening, there is bar seating you can hang out for, but we got really lucky and snagged a table from a no-show reservation.
In all, if you're looking for a French bistro style meal, Lucien is a great option, if you're looking to be seen, then it's great for that too.","time":1649508947,"translated":false}]

column3: Innovative, creative cocktails & classic concoctions mixed up in a trendy industrial-style space.
column8: 134 Eldridge St, New York, NY 10002, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"K F","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108201633919756087635/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxYgjEhl2vtpMh-5VNcY8J7zSIrfuMx_bsnw3Et8=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a month ago","text":"There was no wait because we came on a weeknight. Very crammed near the bar but overall great atmosphere. There is no menu, but we were told most of the classic cocktails are available. We chose to let our bartender get creative, and he was AMAZING!! Just give him a general idea of what you're looking for, and he will blow your mind. I went for something citrusy and my friend asked for something smoky and spicy. Both were phenomenal. I usually don't like cocktails that are "spicy," but my friend's drink was so good that it changed my entire impression of spicy cocktails.","time":1677638243,"translated":false},{"author_name":"wai-kit chu","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115347163257709942620/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxY9QXLeGs-0vPF8ruxF9GI9pq-FVEmXp8yz-ROq=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"11 months ago","text":"This was a pretty cool bar. You gotta get there right when it opens or it'll be a wait. Even though it's a small place you can still have fun and be comfortable ☺

They don't have menus. The amazing bartender will make you tasty (and strong)  drinks based on what your like and flavo profiles.

If I am ever in the area, I'd go back for sure.","time":1650068950,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Meghan O'Donnell","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100106261931963261043/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5R8MqdV1iVh95TMGlrogNJ_YlRqWCiC0HEOLsBUKw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"We make it a point to come here each time we are in NYC ! It's been a few years now but still was as good as I remember. The bartenders are always friendly, and welcome ideas as to what type of drink you would like. My favorite this visit were the tiki drinks, but they can make just about anything you dream up! The space is small, so plan to wait for a while. We put our name in, and wait at another local until there's a spot available. Can't wait until next time.","time":1641409865,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Marc Pilmann","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110540267548416597142/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5S92O4ye_Gjq2Q8AjKEdOWN5eY_WvmiSKeDZ2p6VA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"This is definitely one of the best cocktail bars I know, and I have been to many of them, all over the world. If you are looking for a quiet place, this is not for you, but the atmosphere is great and they know their craft. Classic cocktails are great here and I'm sure their signature cocktails are too. Just mind that there can be a long wait on busy days, which is almost everyday.","time":1648238941,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Elizabeth Tam","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109213508069395321210/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QEdUMKuOB94pffGO809i4lPrg_vf4f35ZCD4e3Lg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Cute speakeasy with tasty cocktails - you tell the bartenders what kind of drinks/liquor you like and they make you a cocktail.

Attaboy didn’t quite live up to all of the hype, I was a bit underwhelmed. I would recommend to arrive when the bar opens or you will have to wait for a while to get in.","time":1659916904,"translated":false}]

column3: Creative homemade noodle soups & izakaya-style small plates served in a colorful space with a patio.
column8: 25 Clinton St, New York, NY 10002, USA
column11: [{"author_name":"YC “Claire” L","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105199628830506903327/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxbGHZ__d327IUPW1j-0ZuiJ7edSe-viGRDSPBjbmA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Cute place, crowded but the staff was very efficient. column3: Trendy outdoor Mexican eatery & bar with lively events & a palm-studded seating area on the bay.

column11:
[{"author_name":"Azeya Webb","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108875046557434715157/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RVtGctmE90hTAtiqc6T3gDD896TzMu_RVB5gsH5Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"This place is BEAUTIFUL. There is a lovely out door beach vibe area as well as the restaurant. It’s is EXPENSIVE. I personally felt the price range and portion size did not line up. I would go to treat myself, a date, or drinks with friends.

Bathroom are outside and unisex.","time":1670024483,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Sharon Kenney","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106753686104517644591/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RFZgUs6UTP0OSoZG5b-bxj2ArCj2Fc_VVVRoe8V5s=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"Gitano Island is such a fun escape from the city. column3: Stylish boutique stocking streetwear & accessories for men in a minimalist interior.

column11:
[{"author_name":"Stanley L","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116391854885354990102/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SjPEA4y2PwtyIy_SLGZA7V6KGaO4YgodLpG8IC1Bk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Super friendly staff and great store!
The clothes and outfits here are pretty decent but a little pricey.
The cafe here has great coffee and nice cookies.
I would definitely recommend the Freddo Cappuccino.
The flavor is a bit sour but expected, and adding a little honey is also pretty good for the drink.

A recommended place if you have some time to queue and enter the store!","time":1655713268,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ashley Catalan","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113279629162620754387/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QBJ73O5v3PBYILK121xLTsNXBweo0yO2ALFiZ7dA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"chill vibes in the coffee shop and store! the sales person in store was very engaging and conversational. they didn’t have much in stock when i visited but overall had a great experience.","time":1649000087,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Z T","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114580267715607375010/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5S5AV2GUu9BUUsgdJRw087jQ33mQ2KypRGXMpzUkY8=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Wearing ALD renders one a bit of a fashion NPC, but the clothes are nonetheless very nice. Service is good, selection is solid. The decor and atmosphere inside is stellar. They make great use of the small space. Also cool to get to see 1985 Jordan 1s in-person, which they have hanging on the wall by their cashier.","time":1659143711,"translated":false},{"author_name":"pat d","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102485570370048058160/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxal9_nQq2Bde4HgPAyikU-MlZZutsqjdh0UEhQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"The best retail store I've been to in a long time. They made sure to offer help whenever I needed it and gave me some great tips on what I could pair items with as well. Best store and staff in NYC! Highly recommend!","time":1672664982,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Omar","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103964083512421411037/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5R6AL_vhQfSDtLdC8kit7VP7vGucdkm2Zbxw7BipqI=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":1,"relative_time_description":"2 weeks ago","text":"THIS IS NOT A REVIEW OF THE CLOTHING. BUT OF A SPECIFIC RUDE RETAIL WORKER THAT ACTS LIKE HE OWNS THE STORE!!!

I am a huge fan of Teddy and his work, have early access on the website and have bought TONS of items and put so many friends on the brand. Visited the newly opened London branch and it was amazing, had a great experience.

Was excited to visit the NYC branch but was completely shocked during my visit. The retail worker had an attitude the whole time and did not want to help. Extremely rude and ruined the entire shopping experience. Ended up walking away without even trying the items (mainly because that worker didn’t bring them to the back lol). Someone needs to tell him that he WORKS there and doesn’t own the brand.","time":1679547095,"translated":false}]

column3: Galleries & exhibits dedicated to artist & architect Isamu Noguchi plus a serene sculpture garden.

column11: [{"author_name":"N V","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106130531967740008421/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TcMA-MrdsWhzGsTWu5EZ4SiylgHX2bh20OMtcJtVw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"Beautiful museum! I enjoyed sitting out there and listening to the birds and even saw a squirrel! The gift shop was a visual treat too! The shop was filled with really cool things to purchase! Had a wonderful visit here. Would definitely love to visit again!","time":1670723737,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Krishna Paul","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116300684034790783437/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RzgW3wusepTaCNEmPWIcaUZqsFoHw09Brf1MUspg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Very beautiful museum with great Japanese inspiration! Really loved all the sculptures and origami. The whole place was tranquil and relaxing. There was a lot to explore and it wasn't too cluttered or confusing to navigate. Highly recommend stopping by for some culture!","time":1658041958,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Bess Fung (bessfriend)","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106765251077100194377/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RRKzUHf_1AMs7aFHHU09cevAAzBWR_hLEnWug2ag=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"11 months ago","text":"great museum. love the displays of quality, lovely and fun sculptures. great outdoor space as well. beautiful garden.  calming and peaceful with lovely chirping birds. the free admission on Saturday when I went was a nice surprise.","time":1650146561,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Mark Chang","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105147647679809443793/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RrpYd7RG0Ok7K6hLvePAYWN29ugIAStWeJJBuo9w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"The staff is very professional and friendly. This is a quiet museum that I had kept missing when I lived in the neighborhood. Should have visited sooner. With the Bloomberg Connect app, you can read the guide on your own device in your own pace. I can see the simplicity in the art influenced by Japanese culture. Also loved the garden. Suggest go in the late evening so that you can enjoy day/night view of them.","time":1670642710,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Susanna Mostaghim","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100282854354597495851/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RpQ3KdE6CRgJhdKstuY1BZCabsaEHssiURlfF7CA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Book tickets ahead of time and download the Bloomberg app they use. This place is a hidden gem. The art is spread out pretty well, there’s a good amount of seating throughout even if it’s a small museum. The art is unique and even if you’re like me and don’t understand it all it’s nice. I like it and will continue to swing by as the exhibitions change out.","time":1645469499,"translated":false}]

column2: The Glass House, National Trust for Historic Preservation
column3: Home designed by Philip Johnson is now a designated landmark offering tours, gardens & a cafe.
column8: 199 Elm St, New Canaan, CT 06840, USA
column11: [{"author_name":"M Harrington","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107343621185430132913/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5S9dj6mYqDj4WoIdumZAJis-wWsXCFR97iPsvqJ3Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"The Glass House is quite  an astonishing example of modern  architecture sited amongst a stunning landscape. The former home of Philip Johnson who bought the land in1947 and lived there until his death in 2005. It really is a well organized tour that originates from the Elm Street museum and shuttles you to the home. Enjoyed the tour immensely and loved the ride with the guide back to the museum store pointing out other examples of modern architecture in New Canaan. The tour tickets can be organized via the website. We went on the last tour of the day which has the most beautiful afternoon lighting.","time":1655679183,"translated":false},{"author_name":"L DING","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109604040086821707798/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxaZ2L__9XXWSAXpJ5AL505qPGEsxaTgfcvEbmqb=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"I recommend going for a self-guided tour. The only thing that I can think of that they could have approved is it'd be helpful if the guide at each building can give a rough direction to the next stop.","time":1660870900,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ray","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103262217741261026002/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxZq3LgOSeaCkF3nDU3D8po2mLQ47CGf3utSR-RZ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"Excellent tour and history lesson.\nThe guide was approachable, knowledgeable and exceptional!","time":1661875056,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ruud Noordzij","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114018890256525294894/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Q5nHGwTzRRkysENymeFpVcabSMsVM18Wdol6hrgA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Fantastic! Narration was the best part of the whole tour. Thanks Joyce!","time":1660083514,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Joel Nunez","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106665234961870677201/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RsRgkbn1x6Oa5U5FTwUUprc-A2iS0ia4GifzKG1Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"An architectural landmark worth visiting.
