column3: Photo exhibitions held in a landmark Renaissance Revival-style gallery with a cocktail bar & dining.
column8: 281 Park Ave S, New York, NY 10010, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"J S","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104580301613836737852/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxY0knoJGvXcZ0Ti65jRWtu-ts3C_hmHYcvg9pH3fYI=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Beautiful building with a good collection of photography exhibits. Very powerful well curated work. The top floor is really cool with brick, skylights and exposed beams. Elevator was really slow, but you could also take the stairs. You can grab a drink from the cafe at the entrance and enjoy throughout your visit or at the lounge in the first floor, they have a DJ playing in the evening. Absolutely gorgeous restaurant and bar attached with reservations recommend.","time":1656005755,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Marco Taroni","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100799378279217437875/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RRMZw_ahvBD_D6ohOeA4loTCX60EYJbaY9BHAsoA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"I went here recently, for the David LaChapelle photo exhibition, has been a great event!
The location is really beautiful and the last floor is breathtaking. At the end we went also for some cocktail at the bar Veronika, was a fantastic experience! Highly suggested!","time":1664913410,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Frank Esposito","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104995162724961076951/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxbRm2J0emgafk5QJduJlIjnCOqR95sw88ddQNAa=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a month ago","text":"Absolutely a F-I-V-E STAR ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ experience !!! A beautiful building is the setting for a visually stunning experience in modern and historic photography. Located on Park avenue and 22nd Street in Manhattan, this museum has a very attentive staff to guide you every step of the way to an entertaining visit. A restaurant, gift and coffee shop on the first floor welcome you politely as you enter into a journey of enjoyable photographs. Currently there is a hip-hop exhibit that CANNOT be missed. The gift shop has unique gifts from Amazing Pictorial books to analog cameras. A can't miss if visiting New York,..And a great time for New Yorkers as well.","time":1676390127,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Miguel Casco Arroyo","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117158813944030784993/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5R7MAHiKBqKCnSmSG_bMWBxyJzUOFhsyOeU5eYk9mA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"Every space of this place is full of art. Even at the elevator you can feel the art vibe. The museography design is AMAZING! And you can go trough with your beverage. We loved this place.","time":1653343357,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Shayna Macklin","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116016640640797856085/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TZ4h0RnUdBw9UzYXhgcmlScRDS86eo2gjeTHjB=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"I decided to come in to finally check out the museum after two years of putting it off due to the pandemic.

It did not disappoint. I was there for about three hours. I love how expertly curated all of the photography is. There’s so much to see here. I  really enjoyed that I could have a glass of wine while I browsed each floor. I ended up getting a membership for my husband and myself. I’m so excited to experience all of the benefits that come with being a member here.","time":1643474570,"translated":false}]

column3: Green space behind the NY Public Library's main branch, with 4 acres, a cafe and other food kiosks.
column8: New York, NY 10018, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"E Edw","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112426636472300010592/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxakG8_Ly-t0D0rzHxhLGFkpvVSGIKmwpA5zTBG6=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"The holiday shops were nice to visit. Great places to pick up gifts for family and friends or a little something for yourself.

They've got clothing, candles, holiday decor, fragrances, jewelry, pet themed socks, and a host of other items.

There are several places to grab a bite to eat. We tried the menu from the Chinese, Indian, and Mexican restaurants and everything was delicious. You can get a small bite from each restaurant if you want to give them all a try or you can get full meals, whatever your preference.

There are enough options for everyone to get what they want and places where you can all sit together and chat.

The holiday bar was also nice and located next to the skate rink. Plenty of places to sit with friends.

It rained when we went and because the shops are inside most were open when we got there in the evening. So this place is a good market to visit rain or shine.

The park is about a 5 minute walk from Grand Central Station and is convenient to get to.","time":1668349385,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ang Estrada","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117173016622721819276/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QtWNh6nvfkNWzk42R0kaDOvtzwz26oSqowwdj9k2U=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"This is a great park with a lot to offer. It's not huge but provides a nice outdoor space in the middle of the city. The views of the surrounding buildings are beautiful. The seating areas are abundant. There are fountains, gardens, statues, and lots of green space. A great spot to get some fresh air!","time":1664076826,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Otília Sepp","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108034944186196272367/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RE2O1feBXKwKH8hZJpBx7MpPafJQt9sIyK1xZOnw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Very nice park in the middle of Manhattan. The movie nights during summer are so cool, best open cinema I've ever been to. During the day you can just sit outside, enjoy a coffee or read a book. I love this place!","time":1656418425,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Aung Myo Htut","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102151441712003257670/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TqjjwoA8SjlTbD7WTBSyy3VR9VnllscpeHh3yF=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"It's the park in the heart of New York surrounded by tall buildings. You can visit there when you go to New York public library and Rockefeller center. Subway is at the corner of the park and very easy to get to this park. The lawn is closed at night and if you want to sit on the grass, go before dark. The park is closed at 11 pm. There are many restaurants. I recommend to visit this park when you are in NYC","time":1661273400,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Melania Simonian","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118034616994273156660/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RXJ03u0-D6FYSiuzAiyxlKi9pHWE3rJICC9qoX_Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"11 months ago","text":"Love this park, special ok sunny days. It’s a very good place to have lunch or a snack. Always clean and it’s super clean. You can find some activities to do there during week days or weekends. You can search each on its website.
A plus: you have free wifi in the park!","time":1650074638,"translated":false}]

column3: Legendary circa-1915 cafe serving small plates & cocktails in an updated historic setting.
column8: 79-81 MacDougal St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Ewen Chen","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108444042147298373692/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Q-AfodOdDB6IR7W9dqpvhOp-uK_JKO0_H7fD7F=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"5 months ago","text":"The pasta was delicious and the cocktail lived up to its name. But the service attitude is really not very good, especially the waitress at the door.","time":1665503768,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Suraj Chawla","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112361659018497304903/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxanIXTdOvrQPtuIxOW-vWhp0kjmxtJyzF7SkjBS=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Amazing vibes, excellent food and great service. Every dish is worth trying. I'd wager it's nearly impossible to walk out feeling unsatisfied after a meal at Dante!
They switched our drink since it wasn't to our taste, and they have the cutest Happy Birthday routine.
Side note - the Grasshopper is delicious and the truffle pasta is lit. SHOUT-OUT TO ROAST POTATOES.","time":1643400694,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Lisa Koivu","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109480630754853374721/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QmfvWOXOE05g7FWbgfF6P20r7GaQ-248nR_Z94=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"If I could, I’d give the food 10 stars. Everything was delicious! I ordered the avocado test and wanted to order 3 more even though the serving was quite large. But the toast was so delicious and the eggs were poached to perfection. My cappuccino was as tasty and caffeinating as it was beautiful.

Service, on the other hand, was lacking. We had to ask for our coffee multiple times. I’m jealous of all of the other reviews with incredible looking cocktails - we never received a drink menu. They tried to take away plates we were still working on as if to hurry us up but then we had to ask for the bill multiple times. Service was inconsistent but that wouldn’t stop me from going here again!","time":1644264604,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Dan Moodley","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104724652999745247152/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QYxWFnouL6SBW4w9n09Qee-pGe4haWX4gB0M4ntg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"2 months ago","text":"Great vibe, really buzzing place. Glad i had a reservation as it was jam packed. The food was surprisingly good but the cocktails still stole the show. Well worth the visit to 1 of the best bars in the world.","time":1675285098,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Alan R","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104210321476400567871/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxYaYOuAvFD7I4K6k3RKGvwbSERFvKAOuHQXboy3rKo=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"Dante has been previously rated as one of the best bars in the world and I understand why. Although they also do serve food, we came just for drinks (doesn’t require reservation) and were quickly seated. The drinks were well made, sophisticated, and there is a large menu to choose from. The ambiance is wonderful in there and it is the kind of place where you could sit for a while enjoying great drinks with loved ones.","time":1671896803,"translated":false}]

Swipe to insert the name of this coffee shop! @blankstreet!

So aesthetically pleasing when the coffee cups match the walls! This little coffee shop is actually a walk up window that I’ve walked by quite a few times but never stopped at. I stopped today because @nudgetext sent me a text for a free coffee!

Nudge sends you texts once a week of things to do around the city from coffee and holiday shopping (yesterday’s text) to date night spots to put of the city weekend trips.

If you know me, I’m an iced coffee year round kind of person, but between this cool weather and my cold, I had to get a hot cup. I’ll have to stop by again to try some of their seasonal drinks. What’s your order?","time":1665354663,"translated":false},{"author_name":"chris caracciolo","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114832815149675760712/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SypSxobjHpWee1WCugxT5w0elD8AF72Uk81LLeIlY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Cool people working at this location.

I drank a Peroni which is an Italian Lager.  The service is very good.  The waiter was super attentive.  The prices are very affordable which is rare these days especially at such a nice restaurant.  I plan to return and try some more dishes.","time":1642955891,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Nicolas Kitchin","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101922159435355255773/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SzfqHEfi2p3KGnwFBHyfXH9DY5wnPDbe3pH3HQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"This is my one of my favorite restaurants in New York. column3: Neighborhood Italian spot serving reinvented Italian-American classics & pizzas in a dark space.
column8: 235 Mulberry St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11: [{"author_name":"Ms. Tran","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114489524569036323718/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5S4F1GOEcSr3Tyoxwqvxo3JS9Ex5ESXjSTo_-Qo9H4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"I can’t say enough good things about this place! Traditional Italian food in a lively (not sleepy) atmosphere with great service. We sat at the bar and everyone was so nice! The melon salad (special), the two pastas and pizza were all excellent. The wine pours are GENEROUS! Worth all the hype - go now!","time":1659480066,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Alex Reyes","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113265240366316896907/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TRmrtxBkCZTv_YxoQY3NKFXd0-OYzJrbaQTxfBaw8=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Always on a wait FOR GOOD REASON!\nWe didn't make a reservation, but they always have the bar and a couple tables for walk-ins. The hostess and server were both exceptionally friendly. The meatballs were excellent, as were their special garlic knots. The pizza we had was world-class; I especially enjoyed that it wasn't too cheesey. The pizza was delicate and balanced. The wine was smooth and pure! I even had an opportunity to speak with the manager and he was great vibes.","time":1657993965,"translated":false},{"author_name":"MaddiezMunchies","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109084120836027151760/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SwppisT3ATcTHsFKm0M_HDmUWjCn8jBjyOoccr=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"Amazing tomato sauce and over all flavor of the pizza! The gluten free crust was thin and crunchy, so if that’s what you like this is for you! The size was very large! The ambiance of the restaurant was cozy but lively. The staff were friendly and fast! Menu mentioned it would take extra time to bake the gluten free pizza but it took no time at all (I was there around 4pm).","time":1663686854,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Kewalee S.","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102972770173499624206/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Qzb8Dgup43GbNdjnSyURP2LGiSOuaN1v1C62kQdw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"This place has become the most favorite pizza in NYC. I ordered Tie-Dry Pizza and  Black and white tagliatelle pasta. I love thin crust pizza, the green sauce is pesto and fresh mozzarella.  It’s so amazing. I also love the pasta. The flavor is good.","time":1658422089,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Taylor Snipes","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115512093841003112505/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RovEHcyh37193eQanki2MHbaAVS8-iYJOE2oj6=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"This place sits up there not just as my favorite Italian restaurant in the city, but maybe THE favorite out of all the cuisines. The tie-dye pizza is to die for. It’s a perfect combination of tomato, vodka, and pesto sauce on top of a perfectly cooked and crispy pie. Literally it is amazing and I dream about it. I tried the baked clams the last time I went and wow. I didn’t think I liked clams but I like Rubirosa clams. The bread to start might be the softest bread in Manhattan. We also tried the melon salad on the specials menu and it was incredible. This is a MUST hit if you’re visiting.","time":1668037321,"translated":false}]

column3: Petite Australian cafe luring a stylish crowd with vegemite toast & beet-topped burgers.
column8: 219 Mulberry St A, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Anushka M","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115959482846079376405/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5R0A9k3dU5VvfAzVNfyh4HyPFYWmNHP5AIdGmZH=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"One time a friend got this delivered and I had a bite of the creamy chicken pasta. It was so delicious and since then I've been wanting to come back and actually dine in!

They don't take reservations, so you'll have to arrive with your party to join the waitlist. On a Friday afternoon the wait time was about an hour for 2 people. We put our name down and walked around while we waited to be seated. It's a small space but very quick service. By the time we were seated and ordered our food it had only been maybe 15 minutes.

We got the creamy chicken pasta and the spicy vodka sauce pasta and I added grilled chicken. So delicious! Tasted great and a good portion as well. We also tried their fresh squeezed orange juice which was good.

Overall a great spot and definitely a must try!","time":1672021538,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Rylan Gordon","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107360286584686603711/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RW7mhe4xhC2gvT8drq6wvniZXkHvXn6Njw0oEME6I=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"We love Ruby’s! The burger here was high quality. Loved the fries! They were well seasoned. My wife got the pasta and loved it. It’s very cutely decorated — the perfect cafe vibe. It’s hard to go wrong with their menu. Friendly service too! Definitely recommend coming here!","time":1660449889,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Kelly C","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112379621681844926710/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QIOemIvCaTiQQKgal66f6UcFaYlbK_RVl8zkHhow=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"11 months ago","text":"This was a small place but food was delicious here! I like the ambiance and mood in the restaurant. It is small and cozy. I like how their jars and napkins has the name Ruby’s on it. There is outdoor seating. The plates were a good portion size, although the prices for food and drinks are a bit high but it’s Soho prices. The drinks were good. The red wine sangria was strong. Our waitress could’ve been a bit friendlier.","time":1650173267,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Weijie Li","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111028255368323839303/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SIspqzqQZnVKyNAqkaalJBNRcRt99n-3T0dQkO=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"Ruby's is an Australian Cafe with lots of different options. Everything we try was super delicious and service was quick and great! I recommend getting the shrimp pasta, the shrimp was so fresh surprisingly! And blended super well with the lemon in the sauce.","time":1668400480,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Anna Pagór","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106746716240071810910/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RFGrsA84aumO0IryNMWtIeXinfFyE8mwJQnRZ9O0o=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a week ago","text":"I tried to get there many times for brunch, unfortunately with no luck. This time I went with my friends for dinner and we immediately got a table. I’m not surprised there’s always a long line, the food is amazing!
I ate burger with lemon chicken with sweet potato fries. Delicious! I definitely have to come back to try some pasta, because it looks delicious!
Update: I went to try pasta and it was a delicious experience again! Also you have to try their watermelon cocktail 🍹","time":1679630046,"translated":false}]

column3: Cupcakes, puddings, pies & cakes are made using sustainable ingredients in an eco-friendly space.
column8: 30 Prince St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Kay Bay","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114355169677522138773/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxa176KxjGySSraQ6zrudr823ItqP-Z3MRB3jg9j=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"11 months ago","text":"Really cute bakery with lots to choose from.  We got a slice of cake for $8+ which seemed a little steep but it was good. We also got a raspberry bar for $4+ which seemed more reasonable and was also delicious.  The staff was really nice and made great recommendations.  The only weird part of the bakery is that they have pictures of saints or some kind of religious leaders on one wall...  Just seemed weird and didn't fit the decor but I'm not super stylish,so what do I know.","time":1651455275,"translated":false},{"author_name":"R. Michael Burns","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114960336923598748637/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QcFSdxD0VjaXAQDdyoPZze6xs7MUGqtlmud-38hw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"I had the cheesecake (raspberry and white chocolate) and it was about as good as any I have ever eaten, neither too dense nor too insubstantial, and absolutely perfectly flavored.  The ambiance is charming and the staff were very pleasant.  The prices are pretty high, but given the location and the quality, it's still worth it.","time":1664651767,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Yeshaswini","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115303506283521935900/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SPtDWQVHE0RVEKcp_zJCFp0US5dAoff2cL5mrkzSk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"Such a cute place and the staff are friendly! Loved the variety of vegan options. The cupcakes were moist and so good! Cannot wait to go back and try more flavors.","time":1668863826,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Nonna Starr","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107363514940535954750/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RqwrBA2uhT_1rCB5tIb2XCao8djA2jfMI6DELtH0M=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"I’m finally able to check this off of my “must try” list. I follow them on IG and quickly fell in love. I told myself when I go I’m going to make it worth the trip. So on this day I did just that. I selected four various cakes slices and a mini cheese cake.

The strawberry shortcake was my favorite of the four. It was perfect. The coconut slice was just as nice 😝 third up was the blackout and last but not least the carrot cake. It was good but I’m not a big fan of carrot cake.

The mini caramel cheesecake was really rich. I enjoyed that one while in the car on my way home lol.

All and all I give them 5 stars  the treats are worth the cost in my book ($8 - $9 a slice) it’s a cute shop in a very trendy area. The staff was pleasant and helpful and the establishment was cute & clean. And if your wondering, yes I shared 😝😂","time":1653968728,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Frances Fortanely","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104225612348270545512/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RxbpY9e3k8Bv1wAdHrgd982as9opTAgZk1rAeqng=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"The Brooklyn Blackout cake was good. I wouldn’t say it’s the best I’ve ever had, but it was good. We also got a Brooklyn Blackout cupcake and a Red Velvet cupcake. The Brooklyn Blackout cake was much more moist than the cupcake. Easy to share.","time":1672261100,"translated":false}]

column3: Bustling cocktail spot specializing in ambitious creations, plus a small menu of gourmet bar bites.
column8: 188 Suffolk St, New York, NY 10002, USA
column11: [{"author_name":"Chino Villanueva (MrDaisies)","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109353334313259249904/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RPEhLaLjfMjH_31QIqGYBDk2JhkVzZHFBuemTZ5Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"I was invited to a friend’s birthday to this amazing cocktail bar. Subject for me, is one of the coolest place to hangout with your friends and celebrate what life has to offer. Their assortment of cocktails are imaginative and creative. This is a place where you can sit down, have a conversation and just unwind.","time":1652916109,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Praneeta Lakkapragada","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110031736148473304769/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Q07PKEFfbLg6vGcTz3MM4gmH1OJwq6LzJkGNtSkTc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"This is a great cocktail bar to hangout with girl friends and chat. They have the usual as well as some unique cocktails. I had their rum flavoured ones. I forgot the names now but they are pretty good. Their service is great too. We were a group of 8 and she was on the spot with all the orders.","time":1635979829,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Julia S","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114122611283409923702/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxan4t7ZQobg_0yqVkazIAH90Ro-57ro0RAMBVaP=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"This place was great! Very cute intimate vibes for a date or a drink with a good friend. Not crowded but still bustling. We made a reservation for 3 at 8pm on a Friday night just an hour before we got there which was great. The staff are really friendly and make you feel right at home. I got the jungle bird which was good but had a little bit too bitter of an aftertaste for me. We also got an espresso martini which was 6/10 (very espresso with very little creaminess but some people like that!)","time":1636471424,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Nadia Savelieva","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101708387752494073210/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QHxCpS1jGxkI4N_CTWItLBggc27ytzNGFRZPrs1Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a month ago","text":"Au pear cocktail is yummy. Really enjoyed the atmosphere here too. They serve hot dogs if you’re hungry.","time":1676815094,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ben Prevot","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117869172769601982380/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxaVJbg0PtVGeQNw3a5iMvmodD1daJQNfSA6NOlc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"Fun relaxing vibe! Had been wanting to come here for a while and I'm glad I finally did! If ever in the area again I will definitely plan on coming back!","time":1663210194,"translated":false}]

column3: Famous comics are often in the lineup at this brick-walled comedy club with several shows nightly.
column8: 117 MacDougal St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11: [{"author_name":"Joana","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101768335166984548085/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SDakfaDYWbr6cr1S1j4RE48jvD-pxpPCi-PcE3jPU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"2 months ago","text":"You are guaranteed a great time from the moment you speak with the bouncer until you love. Despite being on a walk in basis we got a great seat, the food was good value for money and we laughed from start to finish. Be aware that you will not be allowed to use your phone throughout the show. Photos were taken at the end and outside.","time":1675616691,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Jake Mullan","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114112021933008836841/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RmbymcKVk3W7BBBVwQWQ-or9C589r5HhURRiW5Tw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"The Cellar is the place to go if you want to see the best comics in the NY scene. While I would not anticipate seeing a surprise set from a big name comedian every time you go, I think you can rest assured you’ll have a great time. The food and drinks are pretty great, too!","time":1659679070,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Kevin Markman","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114168600700996622195/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5R2K2JhdGcGz_Wznfu_12cKvf324kNN1koi8lgHS2E=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"Premier place in the city for comedy. Reserve to see your favorite that you really want to see. There is Stand by for tickets to Stand up if you are lucky but don’t count on it. Lots of shows a night. Lots of laughs.","time":1671539050,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ben Klepzig","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103066710962157765229/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RhaE5u6DfVdAnnK29Mn4EYZdEk94drKrRI9hi1=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Great experience. The process of getting seated was smooth. The staff were professional. Four out of five comedians were awesome. (One was so-so.) But, real talk ... These are the best comedians in the country at the top of their game. You will not be disappointed going to the Comedy Cellar. Now, we had a special bonus - one of those national act drop ins that is always possible at the Comedy Cellar. Bill Burr dropped in and absolutely slayed. You don't need to be told that the Cellar is legendary. But it is. Phones are placed in pouches (that you keep) for good reason, so I only have a picture of the empty stage.","time":1655764578,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Kailey Elfstrum","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105818164917262548480/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RXMYrcgiZtgoiVwgLEASqZCTGy6podgPtdYDQXjw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"It’s ALWAYS a fun night when we go to the Comedy Cellar. It’s so easy to reserve online. Never stress about the lineup because there are always surprise guests and everyone truly knocks it out of the park. Our favorite host is Aruba Ray! There is a two drink (or item) minimum.","time":1670415916,"translated":false}]

column3: Tacos, quesadillas & more are dispensed from a VW van parked inside this kitschy garagelike space.
column8: 267 Elizabeth St, New York, NY 10012, USA

However, the burritos were really good, tacos  are a bit overpriced for what they are. The drinks are decent also. Been to the west side location a few times. Pollo and breaded fish tacos are my favorites. Didn't care too much for the black bean and sweet potato taco. Watermelon and pineapple juices are freshly made.","time":1650773292,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Curiosidades de Carla","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116343551158217928731/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Tcp_KvFs_x3N7tfVUIQ66CGEPfSZk7OYzGGZNduw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":3,"relative_time_description":"5 months ago","text":"Quite good service and beautifull space, very original. Furthermore they have little drink offer, as they could add new drinks and combos.","time":1667129761,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Mauricio Ayala","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111906358126250781802/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QCcmGYLoAh6s5wrNIb0Vnjuv7A2Cv562H_g7KL=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"I was exploring around this area when I walked by and was hit with the wonderful aroma of lightly fried corn tortillas, so I decided to stop here for a quick meal. I tried the Carnitas, the Al Pastor and the Carne Asada tacos. The Carnitas and Al Pastor were ok but nothing really to write home about, the Carne Asada was great. The meat was tender and well seasoned and the lightly fried tortilla complimented it along with the chopped onions and cilantro. I really enjoyed the meal and the staff were quick and friendly.","time":1655249301,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Drew G","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103616236535631292452/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxYZVLwwUj4u3ssfltufRGmU8Y3abkB0B3TsSTR1Cw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"Walked in on a whim and it was quite pleasant. Got a few different tacos, service was quick and nice. Tacos were good and the environment was fantastic. It takes up the full lot with no walls so you can see straight back, making nice and open.","time":1660683172,"translated":false}]

column3: The eclectic menu has a Mediterranean slant at this small, airy bistro with booths & a bar.
column8: 14 Spring St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"India Lindsay","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102424014986483900945/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TE-VK1pTCCrQycYZZNr1S8sQp8M1bUppPne6jfzA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"A creative and yummy Mediterranean fusion restaurant. A solid choice for an evening with friends and was fairly affordable for a nice NYC dinner

We were easily able to snag a table for 3 on a Friday evening. The staff were fun, courteous, and had an energetic vibe. They easily helped make gluten intolerant substitutions.

The outdoor and indoor seating are creatively decorated with bright Mediterranean inspired patterns.

Must try the crispy artichoke hearts - I don’t like artichoke normally and these literally tasted like fries, but healthy. So good! I also recommend the crudo, it’s small and light but has a refreshing olive oil and fresh herb flavor.

The burger and fish kebab are great choices too.","time":1655085152,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Yi Li","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117707868198276745538/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxbVe4mLUkIeNtgGymEgIYqbszRmQmPfC62Zs_AV=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"Ideal spot for a late weekend dinner with a group music gets loud and there's a great ambiance in a small dense space! Food was great, relatively large portions and overall surprisingly affordable for what we ordered. Would definitely come back soon!","time":1664523172,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Cesar Sanchez Lopez","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112779841628221555868/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RnzigAt7hHb8NznfDg9y9dhyfvcrntnbDZCmHKxw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":3,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"The food was mediocre (salty and mushy), the service was slow and the lights kept flickering. Would not come back.","time":1660862156,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ali A Almeshaal","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113224243471037680789/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5T5NQM9nrvPoLYYsUC8mJiIInS78lHWyse1DqimYA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":2,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Nice vibes, great music, and good food as well. Been a few times, and the service was always good","time":1654902289,"translated":false}]

column3: Laid-back venture serving thoughtfully sourced Nicaraguan coffee, plus muesli & pudding.
column8: 149 Elizabeth St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11: [{"author_name":"Melissa","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102331907432529388883/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TwaGslM2paXgHlR5ZSLtt47kjFcCTeddwlJAY-MQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"This place is a must try for delicious Nicaraguan coffee. It is a true respite from the hustle and bustle of Chinatown. I got the daily brew with coconut milk and took an iced latte with almond milk to go for my friend. They have comfortable seating, and coffee beans and bottled cold brew for sale as well. I saw some gluten-free baked goods, too! No bathroom though, sadly.","time":1657565347,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Mikaela Li","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107531845092314964733/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxZv4lsWvMoWCn_4nhw8Wp4MSBNcMfQYC7VCDSum=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"Favorite coffee shop in the city BY FAR. Top notch quality coffee from Nicaragua + great aesthetics/vibes. Staff is the best. Perfect location but generally not super busy. I went for drinks with my friends and had a good time. It has two environments, one bar upstairs and a more crowded space in the basement.","time":1669579265,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Kevin Sanford","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101828489720325733312/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TGGrJGyTmTP016jnLIhuc7JxgZDiP2uZj1uj6TaA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":1,"relative_time_description":"5 months ago","text":"I seriously wanted to like this venue but the manager was extremely arrogant in the way she was treating a group of Party goer's.
The place only has 1 positive factor and that's the Doorman in the front.
However the downstairs security was lurking at everyone and had a menace vibe.
Bartenders and wait staff really didn't want to be bothered when we wanted to order
The Vibes are a wanna be exclusive venue without the charm and substance.
This staff must have learned a lesson in how not to be customer service oriented from the management here.
There are plenty of other places to go to where the establishment wants your money and knows how to treat potential clientle","time":1666753740,"translated":false},{"author_name":"B G","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108503496037695282790/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QcUfrWy6mr1cG2cxEBjRzo8Rwk5cCyD4dmg0pYZg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":1,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"MID! I do not recommend this place ever!
Came here for new years eve celebration and was extremely disappointed. The tickets were $150 per person open bar 11- 2. I thought it would be a fun time and made sense to be at one place on nye  instead of running around the city. But no. It was not worth anywhere near $150! Other bars I was looking into had a better price point ... I should have went to those places and overlooked this one. The experience wasn't magical at all. Only one tv in the basement displayed the count down and a small group of us actually cared. I thought the whole place would have tuned into the count down and had the upstairs section involved as well.... but no the planners of this event treated it like a regular weekend, it was not festive at all in any way.

The drinks were GROSS! Bottom shelf liquor and extremely strong, disgusting drinks. There should have been a prefixed nye cocktail menu to order from instead of whatever the heck they were making behind that bar. I only had 1 cocktail and 2 glasses of champagne and so did my bf. We did not get our moneys worth for the drinks. Not to mention the horrible music and people! IDK what is was about the place the everyone in there thought they were too cool for school ,, like straight up the typical cliche LES a-holes!

The music was so bad. Not one moment at this bar felt like a new years celebration. And security was aggressive (which is not a surprise as I've been here once before and they were total jerks to everyone)!

SO SO SO disappointed in this place and in myself for paying as much as we did to bring in the new year at the flower shop. I'm so upset honestly. Would've had a better time celebrating in my own home then taking a chance trying to get into a bar and paying for my drinks instead of being tricked into believing an open bar at the flower shop was actually worth it. It's barely worth coming here on a regular weekend.

We ended up leaving soon after the ball drop, didn't even stay the whole time. They also took quite some time to open the doors and let everyone in. If I paid for an experience from 11-2 then I wanted to be inside at 11, not standing outside in the rain.

I do not recommend.","time":1672684404,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Renata Guimaraes","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107512986892398707138/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxbl6_79JoHMD4SvLTX7OgdTm_Zqc-7PzARvHUqV=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":1,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"Basement decor and the meanest bar tender I've ever encountered. Ordered a whiskey sour no egg and the bartender proceeded to yell over and over: " We ArE a DiVe BaR" "WHY would we use EGG?!?!?!???" "THIS IS A DIVE BAR" "We use a SODA GUN????" "Wow that's craaaaazy"
shrugging her shoulders and rolling her eyes. Then they closed at 12 when online it says they are open until 2am. And she never last called us.
Damn, I paid $17 to be yelled at...sorry I ordered a drink the way you make it?
White female bartender with long curly redish hair sucks! Heard the downstairs is fun though? Idk obviously I won't be coming back to find out.","time":1672791786,"translated":false}]

Indoor and outdoor seating. Looks fancy but a very casual spot. Locals love to hang here. Pics from a recent visit. The menu is seasonal. They also do wine tasting classes. Fridays arw Hawaiian themed.","time":1652763897,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Jim Young","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102068810142432543096/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxZcu-IbUJDMjOGZQ_Pnleu1bmfND-C39y37gmWt=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a month ago","text":"I've been coming to La Compagnie over the last several weeks and I have to say this place is amazing and is now one of my favorite go-to stops when I'm in the area.

The staff is very friendly and welcoming and the bartender Leila is amazing.  She takes the time to make you feel welcome and is knowledgeable on the wines and food offerings.  When someone takes the time to know your name and makes you a little nametag for your bar perch you almost feel like "Norm" in Cheers.

The ambiance is second to none with nooks and crannies for private intimate conversations or kicking back for a bottle of wine with good friends. It's good to have a place like this that is classy but unpretentious.  Bravo!","time":1675894011,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Keshia Cameron","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104740218386846371860/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5S64MgI2AhoJg5KyHzx2Pht_lFSwuFMzWbjJveKYhI=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"This was such an experience! Last night, I went here to celebrate a friend’s birthday and I truly enjoyed myself. The atmosphere was intimate and the waiter (I didn’t get his name) was so attentive to our needs especially when suggesting wines for the table.

However, I have some minor complaints with the menu. It didn’t have much vegetarian options although, the grilled cheese with mushrooms and tomato jam was a hit! I was very opposed to this because I HATE mushrooms but I really enjoyed, REALLY enjoyed this sandwich - thanks to the waiter. This place has small bites so don’t expect a full meal.

Please visit this place if you want to impress your date or just catch up with a friend.","time":1664284703,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Jason Cook","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102663183045208092847/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Q3dFqswKA6nl0hh8vZYaS7PCk4qoThiHjgge6JiTw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Really nice experience.
