column3: Buzzy, intimate spot offering a daily changing menu of seasonal Israeli plates & absinthe cocktails.
column8: 61 W 8th St, New York, NY 10011, USA
column11: [{"author_name":"Shab N","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113439847511664706802/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5T6qlPYf6DsPy1QDuoFfmZwp3P6kReaMryqz4iVVA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":1,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"Having been to Hasalon several times, we were excited to try this new place by Eyal Shani. However the whole experience was disappointing at best. The portions are ridiculously small, tasteless and overpriced. $25 for a small piece of bread with diced tomatoes on top or $50 for 3 tiny pieces of lamb is ridiculous. We pay these prices at Hasalon, but the vibe and dj music compensates for small portions and high prices. But Shmone delivers none of that fun experience, overcharges and under-delivers. We paid $500 and went to have normal dinner at another Mediterranean place nearby. Had really high expectations of Shmone, but left disappointed and hungry.","time":1653187104,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Rebecca Lullio","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102130888800535829065/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5R9BLeBRhZ6RzqIk7FAcTFguFTBXz-kSvspE7wr=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"Let me start out by saying that this place is absolutely beautiful and if you are lucky enough to experience dining here, you must grab a seat at the chefs counter. I go out to dinner a lot and I have to say that the service and hospitality and vibe here was one of the most unique meals I’ve had in NYC. The food is so beautifully and thoughtfully prepared, our chefs were so kind and interacting with us all night, making our experience so much fun, our server was the absolute, sweetest doll of a man ever. The portions were generous and so clean w/ high-quality ingredients, there were surprises around every corner and we were treated like gold. I would absolutely go back!","time":1671119586,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Brigitte A","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105919937601995220990/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxb7gsmaP2Mz8NtuRFPaaod3ewZJPaQ5GPr20p4W=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"Truly a delightful dining experience of the freshest ingredients, beautifully plated with the most delicate flavors, perfectly paired with their exquisite wine list. What I appreciated even more was the warmth and kindness of the staff. It felt as if we were invited in their home like family and no pretense. A most refreshing approach with an authentic fun and feel good feeling!","time":1668089219,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Steve Berger","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105623384417468551559/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Q9nuFktuRA2sZVlDvM2Sn22zQEuF5pVci2O9Uh9g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"We had a fantastic experience here for dinner. There were 3 of us and we shared 9 dishes. We had vegetable, fish and meat dishes - everything was excellent. The service was also over the top amazing. Would definitely recommend this place for a date or a small group (because of the space probably not super ideal for large parties).","time":1670788876,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Jas Tanaka","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116959970219538964549/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RUzm2Q8drL_bcdZ2hmOzKanRiTP-IECjg_GG8-Uw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"Super friendly staff, love the dining vibe here. The food was amazing. We ordered the wagyu, baby artichoke pasta and grilled calamari. Good portion of food, and the seasoning was just right. We had a great time here. Highly recommended!","time":1672282643,"translated":false}]

column3: Casual Swiss spot with European rail-station-restaurant vibe & a hidden late-night space in back.
column8: 212 Lafayette St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Joel Imventarza","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104322196747453539419/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Sd68UcC_yu1dWLVbA5sV_laxc7tvwxlSPrg9jM3GY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Went for late dinner and stayed for the drinks!
Great place, the staff is super nice and the give great service. Place is full but there is always room for a new party. We had the racket appetizer, really nice. The butter truffle burger is amazing. The Porto wine was great too, we had the Albariño.  The hash browns are okay. Drinks, please try the espresso martin it was delicious. Will come back!","time":1656889830,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Calum Morrison","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105997739026072135475/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Sw8UiExssoDLuRpzATWDtbQi8ozGInaUymuOnk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba8","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Went for drinks, stayed for Christmas Dinner! From the get go, the staff couldn't have been nicer and the wine was fantastic. With nowhere else planned, we took a look at the menu and decided to eat here for Christmas.
A great menu with lots of choice, every dish we had was superb and our waiter was warm, friendly and super efficient.
Can't recommend Café Select enough!","time":1640485052,"translated":false},{"author_name":"David C","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111387331527243794128/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TdfC5glAwQBMLvq_KGPgroco5YqgpEDp49RHEZ0Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":2,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Food is fine.
The service however is simply rude, not good, they are a bit stuck up. I believe they don’t want tourists in their local. Twice we went there and treated us like if we’re out of place or bothering at the door with our tourist appearance (thick coat and carrying a bag on my back…). The girl at the door is simply stupid… I don’t recommend this place.

I give 2 stars because the food is not bad and the young girl who served our food was nice (I bet she was new there…).","time":1643587095,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Jacqueline Berkenstadt","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114287281439435961796/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TmKA2Q7oYdh-I77q8Z4Y1yPLnF11GKAS8qCSwq=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Loved this place.
We wanted a place to eat a Friday night at 11.30pm, luckily Cafe Select was open and serving food till 1am!
They had a table available. Ambience was nice, full of young people, good music. We had a bottle of white wine, the raclette, a burger and hash browns. Raclette was amazing!
The truffle burger was great too! Really juicy! One of the bust burgers I had in NY!
The hash brown was bad. Had no taste and was completely overcooked.
The waiter gave us 2 espresso martini as gift just because the barman made too extra. They were GREAT! Great service too! Price was really good for the food. All that for nearly $50 (not considering the wine or service).
Definitely will come back!","time":1656768953,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Joshua Tipton","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106730702835691080569/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5ScuWCV1Gv-aB4y3C1JEe2J3i1vnn0xwDnokBqP-Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":3,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"Pleasant outside patio atmosphere. Really nice location to grab a drink late night, unfortunately my first drink was pretty poorly made, but our waiter did a quick swap for a beer and I was happy. I’d stay away from their margaritas.","time":1652902527,"translated":false}]

column3: Cozy eatery serving oysters, snacks & drinks in vintage-inspired digs with live music & DJ nights.
column8: 14 Orchard St, New York, NY 10002, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Sandy","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103563205825679471934/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxafoWYFRqQRzfeOe7F4AsZkV7u2ZtOVnWxqVxhv4nk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"5 months ago","text":"Great bar in LES. Beautiful ambiance, low key and dim lit. They have live jazz typically I believe she said wed-Saturday. They have a few items on HH, their version of espresso martini was delicious, and we also got the oysters which were $1 each and were good!","time":1667500844,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Kim","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118327594943278683048/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5R7p7WznpvLWyP3Bgw-FR5VFZZ2UnYycyNv-IDTtg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"I really enjoyed my time there for Happy Hour. Considering the circumstances, COVID and Happy Hour, I still had pretty good service. The oysters were awesome and the Moscow Mules were delicious. All things considered, I had a great time with a friend at Bar Belly! The popcorn was a fun addition instead of chips.","time":1645666395,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Avi Rakesh","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116024210496051662530/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QNZqSgX3Nwr2wYj_uoWYiKCmHsKIJzV_g5Iqli6g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"A fantastic bar hidden in the depths of LES. It has an ambiance that urges you and your date to open up to each other with perfect blend of candle light and soothing music in the background. Cocktails were very good and a good place to try some new ones!","time":1659638906,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Edward Cabral","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110726792029025262012/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TvpbsyZSPqqAyqGtbYR_BQraQ-Ljlz--hSWz3VBnk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"5 months ago","text":"Had a pandan frozen cocktail and oysters for happy hour. Chefs accidentally forgot one oyster so they gave us two in a little plate lol. Service was great, everyone was friendly and nice, orderly and quick, prices very good for area, and free table popcorn. Genesis was a great server thank you! Will be coming back.","time":1665786614,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Mabel Jimenez","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110266502087381800890/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TbyeZpWsg7v9Kw4XzhcwkErA8vkI7wjdIjag1PtQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":3,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Cute small joint, with a interesting drinks and food.
I only stopped to see the place and have a cocktail.
They have their own variation of aperol spritz, which is decent. A Frozen cocktail that is delicious.

The service isn’t the greatest, I was seating by the bar and it took forever to get my oysters, and despite the fact I was right in front of the bartender he seems to be a little ambushed by the plenty of cocktails request  will pop up. Main reason why I left right after my oysters which took forever to get to me.

I wasn’t sold by my first time here. I’ve heard about this place plenty of times, but didn’t quite have the “experience” other might’ve had. Not sure if it’s cause the time of the day I went, which was right after they opened.","time":1655491492,"translated":false}]

column3: Beer, wine & inventive cocktails fixed up in a buzzy bar with live DJs & an edgy vibe.
column8: 9 Avenue A, New York, NY 10009, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"daniele mesiti","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103919812803298686196/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RftdNybiqMAALJyDjAiVrAcgwcMbTowk-L4UoSlg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"5 months ago","text":"great dance space with a really amazing collection of lights all over that give it a very glowing and chill ambiance. the staff are nice and keep the space clean and organized. this melon drink i had was just bananas! good spot for date night or perhaps to come out with a group","time":1666969012,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Chantal Guzman","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114203493829080807230/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5T9YmHkswvYvjeiqmYaAyYbCoHCG7s51gRF6e130g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"2 weeks ago","text":"Great vibes here! The drinks are amazing and so is the music! The owner came out to talk to the guests coming in and really made us feel safe there. The only reason I took a star off was due to the bouncers who seem to have favorites and are unfair with how they let people in. Make sure to continue bothering them to get in or else they’ll look right past you! Besides the bouncers, everything else was great.","time":1679210844,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Blake Topper","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103252975721546426678/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SyJ1cStK9-tPdfCib_4rDwlyG4I7cf7H8XwrVfYw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"2 months ago","text":"Vibes were good and music was a lot of fun. I see some reviews talking about issues with the bouncers and stuff but I don’t see where they’re coming from. I had no issues with them and all of the staff were friendly and welcoming. They clearly stated while we were in line that they just wanted to make it a safe and welcoming space where anyone can come and enjoy themselves and I think they did just that.","time":1673713050,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Matthew Elliott","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113805140600336795975/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5ScHzCGEDTmwHWjsKy_fkC9zwl5iMay4b_GRITq=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"This place is good.

The bar upstairs is a cool place to chill before you head downstairs to the dance floor. Not sure if this is a regular thing but they were handing out cigarettes for free.

Once you head downstairs is where the fun begins. My friends and I arrived a little before ten to avoid the long line. (Lines can get super long here). When I was there the DJ was playing bass heavy classic remixes. Cool vibe and I was able to dance to most of what they were spinning. If you're looking for a dancy bar this is it. Everyone was vibing downstairs and it's a good crowd. Left around midnight but had a great time.","time":1668929893,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Dasha Zinoviev","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100446265053853861109/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxZiKzJbTBcqnqNnZTcTuCevyUX36lvOZ1YvmGzdWg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"5 months ago","text":"if you’re in NYC definitely come by here!!! Had an excellent time!! Harley was so welcoming and kind. The bartenders were so skilled and the ambience and people were incredible. Will definitely be back!","time":1667028391,"translated":false}]

column3: Retro, wood-paneled bar offering cocktails, wines & beer, plus snacks like oysters & beef sliders.
column8: 332 Lafayette St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Melissa Naja","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107230707591929011626/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Qvx2OLgwyIhqNmdEQ5GJsBGB0-d35xlY5NoThXGg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"My friend and I walked in with no reservation. We were just hung out in the area and saw this bar nearby. I love the vibe of the place, interior and style of secret bar. No name of the bar outside only symbol of animal skeleton next to the door. The host was super nice to us, and we told her we can just sit at the bar because we didn't reserve the table. She brought us to waiting area, but we were still able to order some drinks while waiting. Drinks are fantastic, my friend who is also a bartender gave them a compliment. They did a great job with martini straight up with a twist. For my drink I had spicy flamingo, it is Tequila blanco, watermelon, lime, agave & chili salt. With good service, great drinks and sexy atmosphere, we will definitely go back and invite more friend next time.","time":1661206669,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Stanley L","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116391854885354990102/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SjPEA4y2PwtyIy_SLGZA7V6KGaO4YgodLpG8IC1Bk=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Great service and good cocktails!
The vibe here is pretty chill but not noisy, and the inner furnishing is really classic and elegant.

The blue Negroni tastes almost as a normal Negroni with slightly more fragrance of orange peel garnishing.
The penicillin is also decent with Islay whiskey.
The Dark rain is also great but not as surprising as the other two, but still a great drink!

Also be sure if you could not open a door, try open the door on the other side.
We waited in line for 20 minutes and ended up found there was another door on the other side 😅

A recommended bar in the area!","time":1656265899,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Kaitlyn F","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114417245628648202254/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5R3JA6VsoS2Qg_uLXuq1eF0P5NwWmPW7AcSYqSXUw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2","rating":3,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Easy to make a reservation and got in with no problem! We were seated in the back at a table but did have the option to wait for a seat at the bar. When we walked back to the table we could hardly see it was so dark — only a few lights on at their dimmest setting and candles on the tables. It was also incredibly loud. Their cocktails aren’t cheap at $21 each and mine was mostly ice but they do provide complimentary popcorn so I tricked myself into thinking the cocktail was $15 and the popcorn was $6 to make myself feel better. Overall, be prepared to squint and shout if you are sitting in the back room. Perhaps sitting at the bar is a better experience.","time":1659884845,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Elliott Rains","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102723004350374449500/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5T2kmz4e6Pl-P54aHfFj0PlY5EUq6FIOUpRTI_4tlA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"One of my favorite cocktail bars in the city. A few of my favorite drinks from Attaboy made it over to their menu and every new cocktail I've tried has been top notch. Love the vibe for a date night or just drinks with a friend in a fun but not insanely loud setting. Only knock is it's impossible to get into on the weekends (at least in my experience) and the weekend bouncer is not the most personable dude I've encountered (I hope it's not just me giving off a bad vibe!). Highly recommend you make a reservation if at all possible; you'll be glad you did.","time":1657742585,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Christopher Vu","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103990653370517986617/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QsjahmLo0WF63Js6TyCCCJbbUSflio1zDJs4Lx9eM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Honestly, amazing to be back through the door again! I want to make it my old/new place again! Great bartenders and great drinks! The service at the bar will make you feel comfortable and engaged, super important!

It really looks just as the last time I was there in my memory but a little more polished this time around!

I'm in the hospitality industry and the new team and ownership are gonna kill it and do it justice!

I'd love to make it one of my places to become a regular again but I would recommend making a reservation! The door is tough and seats WILL fill up!","time":1639472687,"translated":false}]

column3: Housemade pasta & creative mains turned out in a charming eatery that has outdoor seating.
column8: 9 Stanton St, New York, NY 10002, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Paul Cheong","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107760199989401025038/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Qp47Fsg5qpbCnNjZieQtdT049t4_9uZyR-IWRXrM0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"With a casual ambiance and a classy touch, Forsythia delivers amazing pasta dishes without any pomp. One downside was that the place was pretty cramped. You couldn’t push your chair back to stand up without running into the person sitting at the table behind you. We were in the workshop-looking section of the restaurant. Maybe the other section is roomier. Overall I’d recommend this place and I’d go back for more spectacular pasta but I’d love to see them providing more comfort for the guests.","time":1668614962,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Javier Kohen","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114955250538652050870/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RaF4oHV1TJUNGwB_LuG1vFVuLyLdyfFfzxx9IbVA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"All the food was good, but no single dish awed me, and I felt the same about the dessert. The set menu was fun in a group where we could taste most dishes. The wine was expensive. The service was effective and friendly.","time":1665108340,"translated":false},{"author_name":"A Booth","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115055562837089678308/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RgyLVq5DnyVfJbilllFLq8LYZu1rUCKPi0Z7iaow=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Excellent meal and service. This is a 5 course prix-fixe menu with plenty of options. We basically split everything so I tasted 10 different things.

The server was great at answering questions on the menu and telling us about the food and wine.

If you want to try excellent pasta come here.

The only critique would be the pomodoro sauce for the rigotoni. The pasta itself was great, but this dish didn’t have the same taste factor that all the other pasta dishes had","time":1658057234,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Louis Garza","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114624641731502314128/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RNzFWCxs4zzpxOJsQhmbIHpXLtzU-EHik9TF1CvA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"Forsythia was a delicious multi-course experience. We went in for the premix frix menu for a birthday surprise, and we’re taking through an abundance of flavors. The ravioli cheese and mushroom combo was a particular standout among many standouts, as was the short rib stuffed pasta. The desserts were delicious as well. The blueberry gelato was yummy and unique, and the pistachio covered cake was a favorite of mine. We left satisfied but not overly full, and I can say that this is easily some of the best pasta in the city. Few contenders exist, and even then Forsythia stands among them. Worth the visit!","time":1664289782,"translated":false},{"author_name":"B Heo","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113112162478745875763/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TrOg61pmffq7nt5RjnmxUL7I011reoiSvW8bY9k9c=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"I had the best dinner at Forsythia. I heard making a reservation is very hard, but my lucky friend got us a table for two. The staffs were welcoming and friendly. Our server was attentive and excellent! Foods were amazing. My friend and I enjoyed every bite of our dining room prix fixe. Homemade focaccia is delicious. Our server offered another round of it when we just finished our carbonara, and we of course had to have it. It was well spent $75pp course dinner. Hope I can come back again soon.","time":1647032461,"translated":false}]

column3: Modern bagel shop for Montreal-style wood-oven bagels plus smoked fish & creative sandwiches.
column8: 170 Elizabeth St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Chris B.","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105699283204011513771/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxaVFo7m2xhuq6iT198D_awo8tZLGpFjf2oyVNB52A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"Supposedly these are “Montreal” style bagels. Not sure what that means, but I thought the bagel was delicious. It was certainly better than some of the more well known “NY” style spots that I’ve been too. Light and fluffy with a decent crust and toppings on my everything bagel. The cream cheese was good and ample portion. The dough tasted fresh and delicious.","time":1660758011,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Amanda Lutz","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115199921024977084743/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SJfgEnQZ8mg6cQmKUAyIAfIMCfQqcYEcOU6Xu2AQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"Wow! All I have to say is WOW. I have not had a great gluten free bagel in years, and today I found one. Highly recommend the gf everything bagel w lox & dill cream cheese (could use a smidge more dill but that's just a preference). Small, outside dining space. No inside dining. Benches for sitting inside though. No bathrooms visible. Salmon bagel sandwich was devoured by my husband as well. Service was cheerful, which was a welcome in this city 😂","time":1663164080,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Kezia Lynch","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113943598139278643041/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Rvp25HdL8w6FzTeyfWAfEv-cOgMhUqEAneQJ2IEP0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Swung in here for a bagel on my first day in the city.

Got a BOCA from the menu which has eggs, cheese, avocado and tomato in it. Absolutely massive so filled me up and kept me full for hours. The prices are very reasonable for the quality of ingredients and portion size.

Will definitely be returning to try more across the menu!","time":1657031023,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Halla Fakhoury","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103142092610710666444/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TfAFAYCL6v5zMQwttkwmXVUcdVd-C14UuK65No1g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"If you’re looking for a NY Bagel Experience, go here!! I got their Classic 2.0 on a Multi-Everything bagel and was totally delighted by their pastrami salmon 👌🏼 I didn’t catch her name, but the young woman working the register was so sweet and made my day. My first time at Black Seed Bagels but definitely won’t be my last! 🥯","time":1669136422,"translated":false},{"author_name":"mermaid magic","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113613502605726391360/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxZtWvWT0xKH_dAeOcDWH9xXsn0XF51wdi6F6Atd=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":1,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"I have been coming to black seed bagels since the beginning at their first store on Elizabeth.. They fave me wrong order, and stale bagels!   The bagels used to be really good here! I was obsessed with these bagels.  Now the store has expanded and their bagels are mass produced and terrible.
I ordered 12 bagels,  rye, everything & sesame. I got mostly white bagels a few oat , 1 rye, 2 everything…😳that tasted like store bought grocery prepackaged bagels, really bad!!
whatever else they tried to give me were not edible and the dough/taste was despicably bad!  They literally tasted a week old!   I will return here ever again !!  Not the same place that used to wood fire delicious hot   bagels, these did not even taste like wood fire, let alone taste like a proper NY bagel when they first started this company!  Too many other great bagel places in NY.  This was my last stop here!! Very SAD!!","time":1640124860,"translated":false}]

column3: Environmentally conscious café with classic drinks & ornamental cupcakes in a verdant, rustic space.
column8: 180 Mulberry St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Kiki R.","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115848813972185201610/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Rjum5QU69_FXAo5IjeOIXchu7sj2xW1LKI-CPtrg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"They just moved to new place. Such a cool spot to grab a coffee. I enjoy everything here.

Wish they could have more space inside to enjoy the vibes and coffee. But its such a very cute little and cozy place. I love the decor inside a lot.

Got ice mocha and hot almond latte which taste good as always. Staff is friendly.

Always be my favorite spot to grab a coffee every time I go to Soho :)","time":1659540014,"translated":false},{"author_name":"angela huang","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103332791631772882782/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RUdA2B8TIhKN91IGRYKDtP9QZkCsEYF5n_R8OS=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"I ordered the plants cupcakes for my friends birthday, and just a note that remember to fill out the order form online few days prior your pick up time. I almost missed the deadline and called the store front. Gladly they’re really nice and willing to take my order.
Aesthetically, the cupcakes look so delicious and pretty, but those taste unsweetened. I got the earl grey flavor, and honestly I can’t really tell the difference. I don’t like the very sweet cupcakes that you can buy in the supermarkets or dessert places, but sweetness of the cupcakes here are just in the nice middle ground. I will definitely try out their pastries and drinks on my next visit.","time":1663904723,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ulyana","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105852252575853930605/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Q8RBlrKI86KXB5nJZRbiUtLaFtkmvtjPWwk48uPQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Update: they moved to a place next door. I kind of was hoping it’s going to be a bigger place, but not really. Narrow entrance and very limited by the register, but still super cute. I just wish there was more space to sit and enjoy cup of coffee.

Such a cute coffee shop. Loved the coffee. Got their seasonal Autumn spice latter and it was great! Their cupcakes are so unique and pretty! Didn’t get a chance to try one this time, but they do look delicious!","time":1643041776,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Rafael F","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110245261063045338893/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QgzRZZFL4WokrG4ybBYWP3thnnWxVQP8BHVniK8AU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Very cool spot in Manhattan.  Comfortable and cozy.  Very small but great tasting coffee. I had the banana bread and Autumn Spice Latte. Would definitely come back. They offer tiny cupcakes with incredible designs and hopefully they're tasty 😋.","time":1637425592,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Shamim Samadi","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112801096111715892447/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RszvM_y0Cq77kChhBPBDmJiq9w0MD6CgorJVxdRw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Such delicious coffee and friendly staff! Refreshing interior vibe. My second visit in a few days and the latte was amazing AGAIN. Highly recommend this place if you’re looking for good ☕️ in the area!","time":1645726238,"translated":false}]

column3: Watering hole with a dive bar vibe, disco ball & a pool table, serving beer & craft cocktails.

Had heard a lot about it from other friends. There’s only one pool table and you put downs dollar to claim next. You play the winner of the previous game not a game between the two of you. Fries are good, they were able to make the hot dog gluten free with lettuce wrap instead of bun.","time":1659466434,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Vidur B","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105743457677263941123/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RJvIZiQi1JBIbFYguSeniuI8xfYeUnIFrYLfzg_w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Retro chic bar with a pool table. Good vibes, good times","time":1642662312,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Brandon Moore","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108554740289066827576/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SmlAil7u5Pev5L3Vmr12Tn-866GEKja2ZdqimydQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Best bar in NYC. People and atmosphere are top notch. If you’re thinking about going somewhere else to grab drinks, don’t.","time":1643048088,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Nicholas Crespo","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108766484279277945420/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxYfvMeACB8xFvMXi0snY43tVdDO8V0fi_zd95aH=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":1,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Came for a drink and was shut down at the bar. Came understandingly but the workers sent me away while I was trying to get bottle service. Was going to  I give $15,000 for service for my birthday but was shut down and told to go away. Cool for a quick drink but they don’t want to make money. If you’re middle to upper class don’t go here because all they care for is volume too much ego to be served a proper drink.","time":1655877758,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ashley Juliano","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106527007770045448761/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5S7tZpwjHhyFGRRhrzioM0QX1FicPOJVNCSF12i-g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Honestly an amazing bar; good decor, good vibes, and relatively nice people. I feel like I always meet somebody new who is willing to chat and have a good time, you just need to know where to look (can get scene-y at times but then again, what NYC bar doesn’t get like that). From security to bartenders, the people that work there are so incredible if you’re friendly to them, which you always should be.\n\nIf you go on Fridays or Saturdays after 9, you can’t complain about the line because you did it to yourself.","time":1647544098,"translated":false}]

column3: undefined

column11: [{"author_name":"Debra Lin","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100806049656212566855/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TC4c1lSJlekWbAi5Fg5la-IcKxTVr43nmknlfB0A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"Great cocktail bar. Low ceilings, not too crowded on the weekends and good vibes all around.  Often time creative cocktails can be too sweet but everything here is well balanced.","time":1672440121,"translated":false},{"author_name":"William Acks","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106644480909246997105/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SNaHFNuVbKMhMxCAazRZQn10rHfmLONfh0Hn8Meb4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"12 months ago","text":"I really dug the flavor profiles of their drinks. The place was PACKED, but at least the bartenders I interacted with were total professionals re: juggling the mass of people. 5 stars for the staff.  However,  the door felt perputually open and there were easily 20+ people waiting to order from what seemed to be 2 bartenders. Which prompted us to close out after the second round, out of exasperation of sensing that it would take awhile to close out. Needs a floor manager. Crowd seemed to average 20-30 year olds, so more mature drinkers will have to endure inane, over heard conversation of how 'wasted' they are after one drink.","time":1649646643,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Samuel J","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105069199333641079717/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxZhpx31IFR1N6VPMqmkM0bzjuWxjymB3BzREa5J=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a month ago","text":"Great cocktail bar! Will be back soon!","time":1676570624,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Bran Cornwell","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110666845757603120535/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Rmi5b7Vejol0okQAi-XjFPJbjM4EcXoCCxlKKi=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"Went in when they first opened for the night just after 6PM, they had a guest bartender for the evening serving some unique themed cocktails. Phenomenal drinks, outstanding atmosphere and ALL of the bartenders are the sweetest!  Management keeps the party going and they have a list of rotating DJ's that really hit the spot!  Come early because the line can get long.","time":1662513019,"translated":false}]

column3: Trendy, snug cocktail bar serving finger foods, chicken sandwiches & creative drinks.
column8: 115 Allen St, New York, NY 10002, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Tammy Liu","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100975909595860282640/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SejSLRpeh7ZdOe0VkVwlD4_qhiwmhtAfhIVF7_ELQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Wonderful food that I’d like to call classic American done right. We came at opening where there’s a short line, but quickly realized that this place actually lived up to the hype. The front room was more of a quick bite place, where cocktails are on tap and you can get some delicious chicken burgers (some of the best I’ve ever had). We asked to be moved to the back when we were done and there happened to be seating available for us, so we continued the experience in a more traditional NYC bar with bar food and cocktails to enjoy.

I actually liked the cocktails I got in both the front and the back. The one in front was sweeter and more of an appetizer and the one in the back paired better with a heavier meal. Either way if you like chicken and a good drink, this is the place to be!","time":1655592808,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Dwight Kenneth","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111924169639245553527/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Q92hL-m9Hxfhr3xtjDFf6qBIzBu4DoRq09b7MzPww=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Great experience.

Customer service and staff is very polite. Very knowledgeable on the cocktails. Water refill time was impeccable. The food was good, but the cocktails were AMAZING!

Need to go back to try the chicken sandwiches.

Make sure to RSVP for back room as it might get filled quickly.

Heads up before going:
Front room doesn't offer made to order cocktails, only cocktails on draft and the smaller food menu.

The back room doesn't offer the chicken sandwich till 10pm. But has the specialty cocktails and more food options.

All cocktails were unique and delicious.

Be prepared to spend $60 to $90 per person.","time":1657230887,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Rebecca Lee","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104064528993586166066/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SjSGRR8Yo8NkBmDBjnotxDjm4-hVcBF2xMeWEPzQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Came here on a Friday without a reservation when they opened. We started at the back bar with cocktails which were very unique and delicious! There were only two bartenders for a large back space so be prepared to wait a little. The wait is worth it!

We made our way to the front bar to share the Thai Basil chicken sandwich which was unreal. Juicy and flavorful, the basil gave it a nice fresh taste. Nice touch of spice but it wasn’t very spicy. Draft cocktails were just ok. Service was awesome across the board!

This is definitely a favorite spot in Manhattan now and I can’t wait to come back.","time":1657542870,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Cindy Yang","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100791926269017563938/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TAkGaItm9TsY821EowGzEHOXjWqTngPLwPOssBFk4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"Drink is creative but wait is long. Food is mediocre. This is a place that you come for interesting cocktail mixes but not for food or legit cocktails.

You can wait in line for the front room but you'll only get tap cocktail and mediocre food. Or you can sign up for the back room. They'll get your phone number and you can have dinner nearby. But you have to come back in 10 min once they notify you.

We ordered the pizza (tastes more like spiked tomato juice) cold noodles (too much cucumber syrup), key lime pie (way too sweet) and reverse Manhattan, which is the only drink that can be called a real cocktail.

Ordered salted egg chicken sandwich - it's okay but it can use more salted egg sauce. Also it doesn't taste like salted yolk egg.

Popcorn chicken is way too salty. Didn't like it.

Given the wait I probably won't come again","time":1668295975,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Cynthia Wu","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113194560676308780027/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5R2bU5j99QDRodupO6cL8cy2VAk6NpfjBEmH6FgzqI=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Best cocktail bar in New York! All the drinks are inspired from dishes like cold pizza and mango sticky rice. And they did taste like those lol. Especially the cold pizza, literally cold margarita pizza in liquid form. Also recommend the mango sticky rice - lots of layers of flavors.

The fried chicken sandwich was insanely good too!

Make sure to book the back room in advance for a quieter and more comfortable booth experience","time":1655776137,"translated":false}]

column3: Cash-only steak icon where old-school waiters serve aged beef in a German beer hall setting.
column8: 178 Broadway, Brooklyn, NY 11211, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Taylor Snipes","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115512093841003112505/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RovEHcyh37193eQanki2MHbaAVS8-iYJOE2oj6=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"The iconic steakhouse in Brooklyn just across the bridge. Cash only in this classy establishment but well worth the trip to the ATM. Wow, this place is an experience. Our waiter worked there for 40+ years and did a tremendous job. I love how the food comes out steaming. They plate everything for you and tilt the plates just enough to where all the juices flow to the bottom, perfect for you to dip each bite for a little extra oomph. The bacon is a must order as far as sides go. Incredible with the steak sauce. Be careful on the bread as there’s plenty of options and they all taste amazing. Don’t want to fill up in that stuff. Some of the best steak and lamb chops I’ve ever had. Can’t wait to go back.","time":1657473211,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Vy H.","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107425451220419232022/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QR2DbAEW7xurWWg16REdM1q_L4iG58kPeKr6GweQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"Overall, had a good dinner here recently!  Hard to get decent reservations if not made far in advance but we able to secure a 9:15pm weekend dinner—the restaurant is still packed at this time!

Got the “Steak for Two” for $135.90—it was cooked medium (med-rare to medium) and the meat was very tender, plenty for two people.  Personally, I didn’t think the steak was seasoned enough for my liking.  Got the Luger’s Sizzling Bacon Extra Thick, and that was so flavored, would recommended getting this in addition to the steak of course!  The Creamed Spinach was good too.

Staff were friendly and the food came out fairly quick.","time":1672430872,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Robert Marmorstein","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113071518502463416716/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Q_arkIz7cpeWo-4LMsCidYNi5tG7zTqoWNNYh_sg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"This place exceeded expectations. It feels like an old steakhouse, which it is, so it had a certain charm to it. Steak was delicious and perfectly cooked, a little on the rarer side of medium rare. Onion rings were incredible, fries were good, and the bacon was also awesome. This was easily the best steakhouse experience I’ve had in a LONG time. Well worth the price.","time":1644247052,"translated":false},{"author_name":"karim qedan","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115821098786984343377/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SX1hngq_LMyVappHKfg-jPLsC-TJQ-xov3vwOZMw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"This was a true experience! We couldn’t wait to come to New York to come here and eat some steak! The food was phenomenal, from the steak to the salmon, to the lamb chops to all the sides! Everything was absolutely delicious! Make sure you get the creamy spinach as well! The service was the highlight! The staff is super attentive and makes sure your happy with everything you order. I high recommend without a doubt!","time":1656482474,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ian Wong","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103609094531896065405/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxbdilBRXsf-wphuWoTl7GvRAHPBYIZEnmx_NezW=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"A meal at Peter Luger was like taking a step back in time. From the first step in the door, you are transported to a moment in New York history. The restaurant has a very classic and rustic atmosphere to it, only juxtaposed against the diners sitting within.

We had the sizzling bacon, single steak, Luger burger, and the german fried potatoes. The burger is a lunch only item and the bacon and fried potatoes were great compliments but the star of the show lies in their dry aged steak. The porterhouse was packed with great beef flavor and is the quintessential item to order. Definitely enjoyed being able to experience a piece of New York history.","time":1670449672,"translated":false}]

column3: Pizza fans trek to this no-frills Midwood storefront & queue up to partake of its storied slices.
column8: 1424 Avenue J, Brooklyn, NY 11230, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Kevin H","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115008109316099949214/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxY2NP74wCXTihKOCLU_5ntyzq1JQBIxYtb00vYW=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":1,"relative_time_description":"5 months ago","text":"I've been to Di Fara in Brooklyn twice after visiting their Staten Island location. The Staten Island spot is good but supposedly the Brooklyn spot is the best. I will say that the first time I ordered a slice was during an afternoon. The slice was delicious and I really understood the hype. What really stood out to me was how amazing the sauce was.

I decided to bring my wife there the second time during lunch and really hyped it up. We ordered both slices and squares as I see some of the reviews here saying the squares were good. We waited over 20 minutes which is understandable for some quality pizza. we got 1 slice that was boxed separately from the other slices and squares we ordered. My wife ate that slice and said it was good. However, the slice I had was incredibly disappointing. The pizza itself was very thin which I tend to find very enjoyable. However, there was no sauce! THE SLICES IN THIS OTHER BOX MUST HAVE BEEN REHEATED MULTIPLE TIMES OR JUST WAY OVERCOOKED. it was very dry and had a slightly burnt taste. The square was incredibly lackluster and felt like it might have also been reheated. You can tell the difference in color of the basil in my pictures.

I was very upset that I had to wait so long for such poor quality. I ended up not finishing any of the slices or squares and just tossing it away. The fact that the quality can vary wildly and then charge a premium of $5 per slice, $6 per square is ridiculous. I don't think there will be a 3rd visit. There's many local joints that cost less per slice that were way better than what I had today. Better off going to the Staten Island location if I'm in town there.","time":1666147082,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Seth Kleinglass","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116734981429847467213/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5R2Xi_PkEBZ1BMRn3BUeJ1sFtaGmESWiayxVx1O=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"This place has a lot of hype surrounding it - and with VERY good reason.  It lives up to its reputation 100%.  The BEST pizza in all of New York.  That is a bold claim but it is true.  They make the pie to order, the crust is incredible.  The toppings are legit.  There is a shop across the street to grab a drink and eat street side. Do yourself a favor and get here for a slice ASAP!","time":1657633348,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Centretard Tardcentre","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107795556692900835809/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxbx0hCF4JWrqsGNTwuDmzN0aHWqtQ2n49Efcwjm=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a month ago","text":"I was in New York for a week, tried about 10 different pizza places, all the famous spots. I personally thought it wasn't even close, Di Fara was easily the best slice. Surpassed the hype, best pizza I've ever had. Staff were great, quick and friendly. Place is real old school inside. Can't recommend anymore. Wish I could go back again soon.","time":1676216350,"translated":false},{"author_name":"D Magnus","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113538838838647821635/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SuWNIrgP07vRGqURE17UclApp4ROiNYxJP4wTs1Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"a week ago","text":"The pizza here is delicious and we were lucky enough to get a table.

four stars because they do not have Coke but they do have Coke promotional items so you would think they do. luckily you can grab a coke next door.

The pizza is delicious and fresh, but the price tag is way too high. $30 for a regular pie that doesn't really have a lot of toppings... yeah just a little too expensive

lots of famous people have been there. we  hoped for the original owner to be there but he wasn't.","time":1679845694,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ahson Jalali","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102814733539616881070/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QSuHWhob9UGgM9ys562cX9M0dOob-ZwiIEdY17LA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":3,"relative_time_description":"a month ago","text":"Di Fara is an institution. In an effort to stay true and authentic with my reviews, I'm going to point out that my experience was not how I recommend you to visit this wonderful establishment.

1. Order in advance
2. Get a plain pie

We went in for two slices, and got square with toppings added. The mushrooms were absolutely not worth 3 dollars.

Favorite part for me was the crust! Could eat that everyday!

I would come back and do it differently.","time":1675968418,"translated":false}]

column3: Landmark NoLita restaurant serving coal-fired, thin-crust Neapolitan pizza since 1905.
column8: 32 Spring St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11: [{"author_name":"D Y","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111704791926399677177/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5R1hoy4X4fNqhctrdQt5wyv_7KCAc5IaIlcsQO4=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"5 months ago","text":"* First thing to note: they take CASH only. There’s an ATM inside if needed. *\nAnyways…\nBest pizza I’ve ever had. My number one has been Juliana’s for a few years, but it’s now Lombardi’s ","time":1666634415,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Denny Brenny","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108390113953476326852/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Tng8uT0A1pCVRD1k2nz4wDJbeF7eEkyoncKVGm6A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"I had this pizza 🍕 way back in 2010 or 2011. Really before the big social media craze. We walked right into store one Friday evening and there was no wait. You could order multiple sizes. It was the best pizza I’ve eaten. Fast forward to today and I noticed it’s super busy and they only offer one size and they herd you and out. The pizza is still good and served hot. It’s just not what I remember it being. I assume the craze of it being “ original pizza place in NYC”, has caused all the tourists to come calling.","time":1640898576,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Chris B.","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105699283204011513771/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxaVFo7m2xhuq6iT198D_awo8tZLGpFjf2oyVNB52A=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"Classy old sit down joint. Came here for a drunken pepperoni pizza craving and was not disappointed. The pizza was somewhere in between NY style and rustic Italian style. It was fantastic. Their bar seemed to be fully stocked as well. A little pricey, but would definitely come here again for lunch or dinner.","time":1660757696,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Gabriela Martinez","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100381327115116080652/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Q-GnrDiSW6Bs0Iv5Pzo9gn3xLNPI0nor3oU8WjBA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"2 months ago","text":"My sister and I came during the last week of December.  It was busy but we only waited for 20 min to be seated. The servers were incredibly polite. Pizza crust was well done and crispy.  The sauce has a nice herb-y taste, cheese oozing with salty goodness, and the pizza was pipping hot from the oven.  The place is a bit small, but there’s outdoor seating available. I can’t wait to go back again!","time":1673766372,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Roxanna Storms","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114319135937008892117/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SPPAPXuSa_q1Y7tYZliKo9hZOw57qwIDnmM67COg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Lombardi's is a great pizza joint! The inside was clean, and the staff was very friendly and helpful. We ordered Grandma's meatballs, this Caesar salad, and the margarita pizza. We also ordered the Italian seltzer, blood orange flavor, which was our favorite thing we got! It was homemade Italian soda. The salad had very fresh lettuce and romaine leaves, and the dressing was homemade with a rich flavor. The pizza crust had a nice crunch to it, but I think the pizza was just as good as pizza I've had in my hometown before. I thought it was cool how Pizza hut, Papa john's, domino's, and every American Pizza chain has stemmed from this location, the first pizza restaurant in all America. If you're looking for the best pizza in your life, there might be other places in little italy, but if you're looking for a nice evening and a cool piece of history, definitely check this place out!","time":1642620246,"translated":false}]

column3: Popular Chinatown eatery famed for its soup dumplings and other Shanghai dishes in a spare setting.
column8: 46 Bowery, New York, NY 10013, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Mariya Pugacheva","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108314379615457570976/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TnmlaxHpYLq7flqHSVqWfVc8QdMmyyucvfJTFRLg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"LOVE. First time here and I can't believe I haven't been here more often. We were worried that since there were no reservations there would be a wait but we went 5:30pm on a Wednesday and got in immediately. Others were waiting in line when we left though.

MUST TRY: soup dumplings (we had the pork) and the scallion pancakes to start. Amazing. I could go there and just eat soup dumplings. Then we got a variety of noodles and fried rice. The portions were pretty big depending on the dish - some larger than others. We took leftovers to go. Delicious - go there. Lots of variety, quick service, so good.

Cash only!","time":1656884084,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Steve M","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111142810401669091574/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxb4K1wYubSlB-fzrHiixgfUnt9d_rrzV4GIHGmf=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"This has been my favorite meal of New York.  We had a wait for our table of 6, but it was worth it.  Everything was served family style.  The General Tso's Chicken was some of the best I've ever eaten.  We also tried each soup dumpling.  The pork soup dumpling was my favorite.  The crispy pan fried noodle was something I've never had, but it was so flavorful.  Food came really quickly.  I can't wait to get back!","time":1647306893,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Mei Wu","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114146915136739160747/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5R8xGd6bVhlYkurcNPzOQPzXdibb59B2J8YSHli=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"11 months ago","text":"Loved the dining in experience in terms of attentiveness and interior. The pork and crab soup dumplings were really good and packed with soup. We had some other main dishes but they were quite average/1-dimensional in taste since it was basically tossed in sweet & sour chili sauce 🤷🏻‍♀️.","time":1652158173,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Nirupa P","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101708916555721992363/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QN2334yG9bI13P9JSBjmeO_BOuQ76YqYIkHyMZuA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Definitely worth the wait.

Cash only.

Don’t expect great service.

But the food was definitely on point. Everything was full of flavor and cooked perfectly.

The soup dumplings are a must. The seafood noodles had the perfect ration of salty to saucy. Every bite into the soup dumplings packed a punch.

Overall good experience.","time":1658607079,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Chontida Pijanchot","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103251253430957882785/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QmHXLXtRHbUwKVsBG8eenp6oG_N0Mcqo8w5o3kDQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"a month ago","text":"We order the soup dumpling with crab which is phenomenon ! It is delicious ! . We also get a pork soup dumpling also ( My parent like it more than the crab since it has no little shell). Anyway, the noodle is too plain, the fish and crispy beef are way too sweet. I actually would like to give 4.5 stars but it’s not allow. The gratuity is added 18% but we gave 35% because the service is fast. A lot of tourists, luckily we came early so we don’t have to wait for a table.","time":1677204436,"translated":false}]

column3: Old-school waiters set the tone at this longtime Italian restaurant and celebrity hangout.
column8: 55 E Houston St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Jules Rha","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113507643470694156632/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SLVAXhqGL3UXXVblcpa8h8qW6G7aRned6-HRJEGw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"I now understand why there’s always a line for this establishment.. Food was hands down so good! A true NYC Italian restaurant with that cozy old school NYC vibes.. oh and did I mention the delicious food and the staff def makes the experience that much better! The pasta was cooked perfect!
I usually always have a to go bag but I actually finished the entire meal! Thanks to our waiter Emanuel for the experience!","time":1664669286,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Mandy Elizabeth","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104518910111115817797/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Tbcyl3Y-hMcdY9PgregD_89BQ7yIdjsEv0eEfDTFM=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Very welcoming, from the moment my family and I walked in. The owner was seated, eating lunch himself, by the door and warmly greeted us, encouraging us to take whichever table was comfortable/preferable.
The food was great. Unfortunately, my 5 month daughter decided to be a bit fussy, so I stepped away to the private room to feed her and missed out on the appetizers while they were warm. But, coming back to the table and sampling the calamari and baked class, I could imagine how much more enjoyable they would be warm.
I ordered the chicken parm, and was thoroughly satisfied. The sauce is great.
I love the atmosphere, the photos on the wall, of all the greats that have been there. It's a nice experience. It's my second time there, I would gladly return again.","time":1643592165,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Mario Diurno","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113153184218100765294/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QRHQg18MTYQJ4IhIeSFw7eN69Edo4O_lR626vRcUc=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"Man where do I start? The ambiance like a an old 50’s movie. The servers so nice and personable Especially Mario! The food is second to none. Hands down best Italian food next to my mother. I’d wait 3 hours to eat there again.","time":1668268639,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ema LT","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101999290039775454868/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SGv8UZ9LNNQ9Qt_GdaCt4bmC7E_GOKr_YvzMKAoA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"I really enjoyed Emilio’s. Lovely atmosphere and the food is really good too. Authentic Italian - with an American influence but enjoyed it regardless. Gotta love it when they leave you the Parmesan bowl at the table! In real Italian style. Quite pricey if you consider that the cheapest wine was something around $85 but worth it considering the overall experience.","time":1671458728,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ben Klepzig","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103066710962157765229/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RhaE5u6DfVdAnnK29Mn4EYZdEk94drKrRI9hi1=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Wonderful experience. The bolognese sauce and pasta were the best I've ever had. So good. The warm focaccia at the start was amazing.  I had to move fast to get a picture of the last piece. My family had the chicken parmesan and spaghetti with red sauce. Both solid,  but not as good as the bolognese. Staff was friendly and helpful. The atmosphere was cozy and welcoming. Highly recommended.","time":1656273169,"translated":false}]

column3: Square pies named for streets in the neighborhood nourish & amuse at this NoLita pizzeria.
column8: 27 Prince St A, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"wendy chin","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105164189863252799593/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5S4krJJZutAh5fE3ux5Vl8O_73HURzS1O6-KOuk2aE=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"I haven't been back here in a few years and have heard from friends that their quality was not as good as before. But I still wanted to try it again for myself and I have to disagree. It is still one of the best pepperoni pizza around! The dough itself was not exactly like before but the pepperoni cups were still on point. Which is why I still like it here. The type of pepperoni they use and the way they crisp just the top still makes this one of my favorite spots.
Just in case you're thinking we like the pizza because we were hungry - We had dinner at 9pm and got Prince St Pizza at 1130pm (had a line but not a long line) and ate this as midnight snack. We still loved it.","time":1655061071,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Liam Killeen","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117899338436634269482/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Smn0oZ43RMFH6ur40ejR4rp9MsRiRXSgjCGZ1x=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"It's legendary for a reason. While a little left of centre when it comes to traditional New York-style pizza, don't overlook Prince Street. The deep dish crust is soft, and the pepperoni is charred to perfection. The spicy kick is also a really nice touch. You won't feel short-changed on the amount of pepperoni per slice, as you can see in the photos - this place is legit. The buttery crust is awesome and makes it more filling than just any slice of pizza. Fair prices, quick service - it's great 'end of night' fuel.","time":1663882019,"translated":false},{"author_name":"David A.","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113490415192295325900/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TofVs8t2keCSOMNXi7GIrGIUoE-t7HCXvmrSgfWJg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Great slice of pizza! We arrived around 2pm and waited in line for about 30 minutes. It was worth it. I got a veggie slice but there are a couple other options. Really great staff running this place. It was fun to chat with the fellas that were handling the rush.","time":1657463777,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Binita D","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114667197148108169690/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxZGQB15WXka0uQ2Nzw--nkFM2c4G2Na7KWxBlrapQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"We were craving some pizzas and stumbled upon this place. We ordered a veggie and pepperoni slice. They were both so delicious! Absolutely loved the thick cut pepperoni. There is no indoor sitting and can’t stand there either but we didn’t mind. Will definitely be coming back!","time":1643725439,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Samad Kadri","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108962687110578132560/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SlTJO-S01bmjjIDbq0eEvNiz7TSVMxavujPkczeA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"in the last week","text":"This will be one of the best pizzas you’ll ever have. And I’ve been to 25+ pizza places in NYC. I’m talking about the square slide they’re known for.

There’s just something about how they make the bread. It is crispy and fluffy and chewy at the same time. Definitely worth the hype.","time":1680318806,"translated":false}]

column3: NoLita branch of mini chain of cafes serving couscous and other French-Moroccan standards.
column8: 242 Mott St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"ariana c","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111276184285240981701/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxZS6swtEW-KHKe_2NHlJsG4anWz4KfHJFpiGRN8=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"My favorite neighborhood spot of all time. The food is consistently tasty, healthy, wholesome, and well priced. The wait staff are all lovely people that get to know the neighborhood. We went to Gitane in Brooklyn for the first time and the vibe was consistent across locations. Much love for Gitane.","time":1654450056,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Kathy D","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108572646020757568872/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxapPlByFd80aXp5M06wAhTskeGv5dqa5Aizn5o-=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"Stumbled upon this place and had breakfast.  Very cool old school restaurant.  Service was great and most of our food was amazing. Baked feta was pungent in the best way. Hummus was light and tasty. Overall we loved what we had to eat only dish that wasn’t a hit was the meatballs and rice, it was very under seasoned. All else was great and we will definitely return.","time":1672245931,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Deanna Y","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110761612773645314381/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5T5YnoCQ-HKJEhIex5VIk1fvfL6zNaqS4-aE3AwP6w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a month ago","text":"Pretty outdoor place near soho .

We went on Wednesday afternoon and the place was crowded .

The outdoor seats are fabulous for brunch on a sunny day .

The servers did a great job although it is shot-staffed. It took awhile for them to come back to the table.

I recommend Mimosa , the Oj is fresh .
DO NOT recommend green tea tho .","time":1676590882,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Nils Paellmann","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112715394850780426965/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SMEkjtHBO9JB6ogiih-1fZQ2N74lLtgeyjw8V9EA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"Lovely French-Maroccan restaurant two blocks from the New Museum. Beautiful decor and great service. The salmon I had and the smoked trout bowl my daughter had were delicious. Reasonable prices too.","time":1668214906,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Sonia Mae","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100896768002434950880/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5S1usxbLRBaE7wthuDCU4fWO2Bh7BsmsdZoqtwRsA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"The classic brunch spot that introduced me to avocado toast! I have attempted to replicate the toast on my own, but it is a standout in how they make the avocado. I’ve been going to this place as a visitor and now as a permanent resident. It’s located in a picturesque area in Nolita. After brunching here, you can roam around the area &  people watch at the Elizabeth garden. My go to dish is avocado toast & the cous cous with the side of sausage. The cous cous can be shared with your dining partner. Today my dining partner suggested to share the blossom waffle and oh my, delicious! The meatballs is another shareable dish that is outstanding. I normally order a mocha latte & get excited for the paw art. This time around, none. I was a bit disappointed to not have the paw art & the chocolate that accompanies it; but I still enjoyed the meal regardless.","time":1637428172,"translated":false}]

column3: Sandy stretch of public beach mostly used for sunbathing, swimming & picnicking.
column8: Lilly pond lane, East Hampton, NY 11937, USA
column11: [{"author_name":"DWF","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107259327006098285664/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxboz6sOLRYwfl1SX8OOgtIZc6Tav41zc5ifZKs=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"We love Georgica!! It’s a fabulous beach with Main Beach vibes but quieter and a little more rustic. If you’re visiting in season (May 15 - September 15) you’ll need an East Hampton VILLAGE (not town) parking permit.
