column3: Hopping seasonal fish house in casual beachy digs with wainscoting & patio tables.
column8: 277 Pantigo Rd, East Hampton, NY 11937, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Matt Scott","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105758669181874715973/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxaKHgDTFGPfMR1ARnMqzeaaTc_s50sKytTT-fWK=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":3,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"New England Clam Chowder was delicious! Also had the Lobster Roll (cold). One of the best ones I've had! The roll was perfectly heated up! Amazing!

UPDATE:
Came back the next day and sat for 20 MINUTES before anyone even asked me if I wanted water. Watched 4 other tables in my section get seated, drinks and orders in before I was even approached by the same waitress serving those tables. Must because I was alone and the others were 4+ in party...so bigger tip for them.

UPDATE:
Tried the hot lobster roll with onion rings. Was delicious. Onion rings were perfect. No drink refill offered this time. Service lacks","time":1661807210,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ruxandra Bklyn","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116113776941109054373/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RUP2wU8BN-0Bx2pKyyB4AOSSET32BpIvYlJm-S0HY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"Casual and cool spot with good food and EXCELLENT service. Everyone was super-sweet, from the hostess who offered me a hoodie because we ate outside and I was cold, to our waitress and everyone in-between.
The food came out fast on paper plates with plastic cutlery, not a big deal, since the quality of food was very good, and the beer fresh and cold. They must have a very efficient kitchen, because the restaurant was packed.
The inside looks great, the outdoor space is very pretty and manicured.
The bathroom needed a wipe, but the place was bustling with people, so I’d cut them a little slack. Will visit again.","time":1652752415,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Stacey Turnbull","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111347739153477801716/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TEhKtHLHmr0O2qwcQpK2AntZLEqMOT6KNYrfhSs9k=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"6 months ago","text":"Came to Bostwick’s on a cold and rainy afternoon during a girls long weekend. Definitely getting into soup weather so the lobster bisque and clam chowder were just what we needed to warm us up!

Our server Maria was adorable and so helpful and happy — as was the rest of the staff. Friend also got fish tacos which they said were delicious.

Would definitely visit again if I come back to the area.","time":1664842558,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Joshua Fields","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114333042282625349690/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RIDXF-k9H_abM0YtP8N0lFgJTq4QgMIQah22nyNFw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"From service to food, this place was a relaxing and fun experience through and through. The lobster bisque is a must have, $10 for a hearty soup is an absolute steal! The baked clams are large, delicious, and worth the price. Lemon puts these on another level. Lastly the Fish and Chips are a staple, high quality fries and delicious hot fish. Would easily come back here again, great lunch spot for friend groups and families.","time":1656101721,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Kevin L","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107418544706703066528/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5S2PW3Wr4MLniQl9IYuu-5df5MP32b3hrlK2ZO_HA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Good attentive service and has a nice local vibe, but the quality of the food is inconsistent. Came here in April 2022 and had amazing lobster rolls that tasted juicy, tender and fresh. But came again in July for dinner and order the same lobster rolls- the edges of the the meat was dark dried out (like it was sitting under at heat lamp for too long) for the hot butter roll while the lobster chunks in the lobster salad roll was over cooked and chewy.","time":1659243466,"translated":false}]

column3: undefined
column8: 75 Thompson St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"JiShun Zhou","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118119258912565996361/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxYdl-WPrNXNImbsT0H55cihXXiF2iJslCWnBY2g2w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"This place is an absolute must for Italian food!
The dishes are so authentic - the lasagna was like the one back home in Bologna, and the arancine were succulent. Incredibile!

The waiter was super nice, and the ambience great.

They have a lunch special which turns many dishes to a very convenient $11.95 per dish price. An absolute steal! You can’t get it anywhere!

Super recommended for lunch, a date, couple or small groups.","time":1643873370,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Manu D","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103958013075789094604/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TV3m4KDoSLP09Z8raJjzSN6KcqwrglyQf035XE=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"12 months ago","text":"The atmosphere is very nice and the servers are very helpful. The food is tasty, but by far my favorite dish was the one the waiter indicated to me, the Tagliatelle Verdi con Ragu topped with black truffle, looooots of flavor just the way I like it. Next time I’ll come during the week since they have lunch specials!!","time":1649513246,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Mike Lawrence","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111518195746939358674/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TQWIojBjNxE2x2ys247R2uu7YvogblweR2zN87buE=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"This is by far the best Italian restaurant we have been to in NYC (or even outside of Italy for that matter). The selection of menu items is small, but it doesn't matter because everything we had was amazing. You can't go wrong with anything on the menu. We will definitely return when we are in NYC. Get a reservation!","time":1654175937,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Jennifer Liang","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101860656302433196626/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Rr4le9ub_P4wPmFncW1LcLjks76UNxoFLc7i6OmA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Amazing Italian food! They have a really nice staff and great ambiance, we came during the lunch hours and it was quite busy! I would recommend the fusilloni with scampi and checking out their seafood appetizer. The portions are just right and you get pretty full by the end of the meal. Definitely check out if you’re around the area and craving Italian! Do make sure you have some time on your hands (around 1.5 hours) as it does get quite busy around meal times and he wait for food can be a tad bit long.","time":1657109670,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Nina Brajdic","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106964849530227950180/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QKgQI6c8q7_n-8RfJglbu-_WCghA2jWwA-3eDY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"I’m very big on Italian cuisine and I love authentic places with real Italian food - this is definite one of those!
Fennel salad was so refreshing! We had octopus with burrata - great combination with crispy bread. Loved Spaghetti allá Norma with eggplant. And I don’t usually like cannolis, they are always so sweet and heavy, but this ones were the best I ever had! I even forgot to take a picture before I almost finished them!","time":1654833039,"translated":false}]

column3: Restaurant & lounge featuring upscale French & Italian bistro fare, plus wine & cocktails.

And then this place is not reservations.He is a racist and the worst restaurant I have ever been to. ,.","time":1679108464,"translated":false}]

column3: Expansive bookshop & cafe stocking bestsellers & hard-to-find titles & hosting author events.
column8: 134 Prince St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11: [{"author_name":"Manuel Hernandez (Manny)","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101805331078691934193/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Qy0yTre3SnJNZ-XiDIv-m-zcd6ZrIOQMkOe2gcMPQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"Been meaning to visit this bookstore for some time. It was worth the wait. They have an amazing selection. I was happy to see they even had a nice couple of shelves of novels and poetry in Spanish downstairs. Also, can’t go wrong with a a four legged staff member helping out! 🐶","time":1668182054,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Elizabeth Hadden","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118003529071655071373/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RJFkuiIY3Q_TwZpxPEVDQiFaxe8XB9P1anC-_Zdg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"One of my favorite bookstores in the area! They have some of the most unique books and even zines/local publications. They also have really helpful recommendations and friendly faces to help you find the right book.","time":1648948778,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Marion NYC","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104231099559936710641/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Thyq_hN_JgWLMPj2TwscGZFIOpElRydblUPkMqrw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Beautifully layed out bookshop. Friendly staff.  There are plenty of fabulous books to choose from.  Two level of books but they also sell various things.  Look up when you’re there to admire the hanging books.  Check this place out when you are in the Soho area!","time":1629380631,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Sarah Myers","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109824828559101013936/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SyUsUatLRu1oyanR7cxdbM2Q_09tmLpUpwZ96XqpQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"My favorite bookstore! I've been coming here for five years. They always have unique and hard to find books... but not just any frivolous story. Each rare book is a hidden gem with quality writing. I am always impressed every time I set foot in here. Oh, and the book events attract some amazing talent and moderators!","time":1671169155,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Michael Shaoul","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107697005281436360813/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxbucBEGp6c8Lq3JtXJ4Fl1VZ-Gp9Qj3SoFaWg3N=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"2 months ago","text":"One of the last independent bookstores in the city. As vibrant today as it was 20 years ago. Great selection of books. Only quirk is that fiction is sorted by country author comes from which sometimes makes it hard to find things if you only know the name..... Otherwise just great to see them keep going","time":1674504278,"translated":false}]

column3: Intimate eatery serving brick oven pizzas & homemade Italian pastas such as gnocchi & linguini.
column8: 146 W Houston St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"JiShun Zhou","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118119258912565996361/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxYdl-WPrNXNImbsT0H55cihXXiF2iJslCWnBY2g2w=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Small restaurant, but great vibes!

Very authentic Italian food! Especially the pizza - fabulous! The dough is light and ingredients fresh. You wouldn’t feel too full after having a whole pie by yourself.

The pasta was very good too - you just can’t go wrong when your have such good quality ingredients.

The house was so nice to treat us an extra dessert! What a great way to end a dinner!

Super recommended!","time":1641864121,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Paul Haber","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108966353265627863740/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RJM_lP90HYTuCr2hHWNSIEdUbPNgbAekRjGrs91g=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"5 months ago","text":"Found this place simply by walking by and hearing the buzz inside. What a great find. This spot is the real deal. Amazing pizza with a luxurious crust. Pasta made to perfection. I tried the truffle pizza special and it was divine. Had to try a past as well. Went basic to taste how they make a traditional red sauce. It did not disappoint. It was bright and rich. Just note this place is small. You will probably have to wait for a table.","time":1665756189,"translated":false},{"author_name":"ReedH","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115878967810096426328/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxaX9nNDSqS22NwMdKB0D114ggfsW0azMrGGZiIb=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 months ago","text":"I’ve wanted come here since seeing it listed among the top 50 pizza restaurants in the world, and wow, it is a gem! We had two pizzas - one a margherita and one with truffle sauce and prosciutto. Both were excellent. I typically like my crust crispier than they do here but the quality of ingredients more than made up for it. It’s a small place, casual and full of Italian pride. But what really makes this place a star is the service. These guys are having fun and want to make sure you are too. It was a quality I find often lacking in NYC restaurants and definitely one I want to return to.","time":1670630956,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Peggy A.","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113155821330992910734/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RA5b8hgqLmWkzanSDo7SmOqZ707i5BqwreDC9slw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"Our son recommended Song' E Napule. I thought I wanted NY style pizza but this is wayyyy better than any other in NYC. BEST thing I ate on this visit! We had the Pizza Parmigiana (even non eggplant Parmisan lovers will LOVE this one)and Salsicce E Friarielli (the sausage is imported and the greens are a perfect campanion). The service is top notch and warm and welcoming. A trip to Italy couldn't have topped this!","time":1668098014,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Alex Kontopanos","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112725200435609261415/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TEajIWwjUvu8-mqF_X_ffpArOvLvc5bIFJMWNI1lQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"Small intimate restaurant with authentic cuisine. It’s a tight space so you’re very cozy with other patrons. Definitely feels like you’re transported to a small family run business in Italy. A bit on the louder side so wouldn’t recommend if you’re looking to have conversation in hushed tones over a meal. Pizza was phenomenal, our pasta dish (creamy truffle sauce with fresh truffles) was just okay, and then for dessert - tiramisu was decent, and ricotta pear was also decent. The pizza was the star of the show for us but would come back to try more and enjoy the vibe!","time":1669864753,"translated":false}]

column3: Classic Thai dishes & drinks by a lauded restaurant group in a kitschy-cool, diner-style setting.
column8: 186 Mott St, New York, NY 10012, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Melissa","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102331907432529388883/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TwaGslM2paXgHlR5ZSLtt47kjFcCTeddwlJAY-MQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"We came for lunch and we would go back in a heartbeat. We really enjoyed the Thai twist on the diner concept. The outdoor seating was great and the food was fantastic. We ordered the Thai disco fries to share (good for two people) and they were delicious. I ordered the som tum salad and I added shrimp. It was super refreshing and very large—easily shareable with two or three people. My friend ordered the rice noodles and added chicken, and really enjoyed it. Everything we ordered had some heat (as expected) so be mindful of that and ask your waiter if your heat tolerance isn’t as high!","time":1657564993,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Kim Dillard","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118222409003637657700/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5T-2Zz3rH6eEXWld91Br3eNbwpAMhc4uaTuBkU6Mw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Met friends for brunch. In true New York weekend brunch style… there was a 40 minute wait. We finally got our table and it was worth it! The food and drinks are delicious here!

If you love spicy Thai food, this place is a great choice. I’m not sure what the drinks or dishes were called because my friends ordered, but I had some of everything and it was all delicious!

The wait staff was kind and attentive.
We will be going back!","time":1659929366,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Michael Guess","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116339218744238912570/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Rn_4isEDBynfxCmUWVgg38az67FieCsBwnW8SONg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Beautiful “gold-meets-new” dining room. The food and cocktails are both really fun takes on classic Thai dishes with a twist of NYC.

Raw dishes are especially plated beautifully, and the entrees don’t shy away from bold flavors. I can’t recommend the crab fried rice enough, I think it’s the best version of the dish ever made.

Very decently priced considering the portions and level of cuisine. Arguably the best Thai fusion restaurant in the city.","time":1656600465,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Priash P","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111108401187236808658/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5RCdwNmOe_27-PQ-nY6ex31pQDM59OeHoPRLJcWzFE=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"I had a great time for lunch at Thai dinner.
The food was excellent.
The spice level was perfect. But I do like extreme spicy Thai food.
The reason for not giving 5 Starr is service wasn’t that attentive. I felt left out. Also, it was late lunch so the place wasn’t that busy either. Besides that everything was good.","time":1657586690,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Chloe Scott","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111719449123780531197/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SV7GvO4DPbH-bIumrflH7GYGjmRwO7s-8Q8oLrLMU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Fantastic food! Pad see ew was phenomenal - the noodles and sauce were perfect. Also the FRIES! The curry sauce was delicious. Great drinks, albeit expensive. Clams were great too! All in all a wonderful experience.","time":1655218739,"translated":false}]

column3: Melbourne-inspired coffee place offering Australian-style espresso drinks & cafe fare all day.
column8: 55 Greenwich Ave, New York, NY 10014, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Daithí Kilcourse","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113613906812319726394/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5QlEVlOLkIGA8UJM719PcK60iU3AFLkstuWuyupfw=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba8","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"7 months ago","text":"We went here today for coffees and the ladies looking after us were wonderful. Easy ordering and we waited less than five minutes for them to come out. Reasonably priced. The cafe was nice and clean with plenty of seating inside and outside.","time":1660689543,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Jea Kim","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117730837401207768949/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5S-RrvhHBqHtr579_DQqge-lEYq98BagDSKfEHf5Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Bluestone Lane used to be one of my favorite places to drop by for some avocado toasts and coffee, and I was excited when I found this brunch cafe near Greenwich village. The place was very crowded during my visit, but I was able to expedite the ordering process as orders were placed and paid via their website linked to their QR code.
Got the avocado smash, seasonal roasted carrots, and the Aussie Iced latte, and everything came out fast. The avocado smash wasn’t a huge upgrade from their avocado toasts in their regular cafes, but I still enjoyed the extra garnish and the artsy presentation. Roasted carrots on the side had a hint of sweetness, and its combination with feta cheese and walnuts was amazing. Aussie iced latte was also a good substitute for dessert, and overall, it was a healthy and satisfying brunch experience.","time":1646714331,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Kierra Hutch","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100287649564788668073/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Qg1JqXrYtAjuqFYohdu5u_csNPFMtcoJwCQCdatQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"9 months ago","text":"Refreshing scene as though your by the beach. I’m Australian and it was recommended to come here for a good proper coffee which I was not disappointed. Menu looks delish also will be back to try brunch next ! Staff were great friendly and helpful. They tailored to my particular coffee order. Thanks Sophie for understanding my particular coffee taste :)","time":1656699883,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Ryan Herron","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109522107142388168544/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TShACnTM1wf5pMjmb0djHv5UL2EV61ud2CQ-Cq=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"3 weeks ago","text":"Very cute cafe in the West Village. While Bluestone is all over the city, this location has a particularly quaint atmosphere.

We ordered the rainbow bowl and brekkie board (avo smash + granola) and really enjoyed them both. Would highly recommend!","time":1678567708,"translated":false},{"author_name":"A Egeli","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116230745032030035833/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SJLBa5Xw8Va90O1WExscqrkOs_Ze2KQz96ToKA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a month ago","text":"I returned from the hospital a week ago. I was overwhelmed by the convalescence, the side effects of the pills, and the general new ineptness. I have been ordering from Bluestone every morning from BS or one of my friends have.
The food has literally made me feel so loved. It comes so fast. The coffee is perfect. The smoothie has  little bits of ice in it. It’s so soothing.
The food is clean and cleverly nutritiously balanced. I needed a big brekkie today. It was decadent and killed the nausea immediately. I never thought I would be writing such a huge review but I guess I’m still discovering the little love nooks in the city. Thank you Team BL","time":1677090935,"translated":false}]

column3: Cafe by a Brooklyn roaster serving coffees & pastries in a plant-filled space with a skylight.
column8: 18 Grattan St, Brooklyn, NY 11206, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Brett East","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100604927999107150066/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SyfVOWelwsZXct792Z4nM1mKEctHu2gtYuxXP49G0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"2 months ago","text":"A really cool vibe, very trendy and the coffee is apparently great for people really into their coffee. I liked mine, but as long as it's a good flat white then I'm happy.
They serve sparkling water with each coffee and have a small selection of pastries.
I saw a bunch of no laptop signs around, but I'm not sure if that applies to everywhere or just the seats we were in.","time":1674410715,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Don Holly","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102715512924922344659/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxacN-ruLycfaZFgx0ZA_txEAyj1VCT1HZUJ2ZHO=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"High quality coffee beverages.  Fairly fast service.  Even though the line was 20 people plus, I think I waited no more than 8 minutes to get my order taken and delivered within 2 minutes of that.  Espresso was deliciously prepared, I got a Cortado and the milk was perfectly frothed, with fun art on the top.  The space is small, and so there was not enough space to stay as they were so busy - easy to understand why they are so popular given how good they are operationally, have great coffee, and the coffeehouse vibe was very positive and comfortable.","time":1668296230,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Joseph S","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104772292373437265603/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5StC4g5gIJ31_EkvhtIQKzPobgxLVnzcOEA218-Ug=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"11 months ago","text":"Was nice to visit a specialty coffee shop which isn't just about the ambience. They do some quality pour overs with some nice beans. Was worth the trek to check it out. Great staff as well. Very friendly and recommended me a very tasty pastry which I won't out since I don't want it to run out when I'm in. Ask them if you really want to know 🐶 hope they continue to do well.","time":1650754476,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Teresa Chou","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118112642030434776343/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5Se6_gQ1SoSzq3uKcd05j339EZY5_k6SoAbqVj7bA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"2 months ago","text":"Impressive!
My first time here and i love it! The staff is friendly and professional. Follow the staff’s recommendation is the right choice. I personally love pour over coffee with floral flavor, so we ordered the $10 one and I LOVE IT!  Also the almond croissant is so good too.
Price: good!
Recommend: everything 🤣
Product: a bit pricy. $24/coffee package
Vibe: chill and beautiful
Seating: only few seats
Tips: dog friendly","time":1675305945,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Kiariladyboss","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110444959236507042957/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SU5RZCAkD5w1oeODD2inmtOQocH6w__pu_Z4TmzaU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"10 months ago","text":"I had Sey Coffee on my coffeeshop to check out and i finally made it on a beautiful aunny day of May. The vibe is great! There are few tables that won’t allow you to use your laptop and other that will allow you to use it for just a couple of hours. Loved the plans and all the small detlails. My oat latte and sweet were both delicious, i paid $10.
The chocolate caramel sweet was gluten and dairy free.

I will for sure go back!","time":1652402116,"translated":false}]

column3: undefined
column8: 152 2nd Ave, New York, NY 10003, USA
column11:
[{"author_name":"Austin Graff","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101810068829626301924/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5T6m7JZa7SFm2LnGTecwab-sRvsn-f3bIFIvYXLGg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba8","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"a year ago","text":"Recently returning from a Copenhagen trip where I discovered cardamom buns from a magical bakery called Juno, I had to find cardamom buns in NYC. They aren't Juno's, but still worth standing in line at La Cabra NYC. They sell other pastries, but the cardamom buns come out fresh from the oven throughout the day. The texture and the cardamom really pop creating a divine pastry.

They have a popular coffee bar with a full coffee menu.

There's inside and patio seating.","time":1644892122,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Natalya Vershinina","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115695596376102216575/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/AGNmyxZnFl2WVrxgmxtEhnRSrVYeM_e_xNYdoDMmfeKe=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Bakery coffee shop in East Village. Amazing spot to get breakfast. Spacious inside with plenty of seating area outside to enjoy great weather. Everything backed fresh daily choice of delicious bread ,very tasty croissants and you have to try cardamon bun flavor and texture I can’t explain that’s why you just have to came one day and try yourself.","time":1659267866,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Kate Kay","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110310624134519780028/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5SdFmpygmsw1ptSeWolshO0V55lsOSGJWyBX6byNQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":4,"relative_time_description":"4 months ago","text":"🕰️ Very busy spot, nearly impossible to snag a table and about 10-15 min to order. Would consider it a great bakery ahead of being a great coffee shop

🥐 I ordered the chocolate croissant, cardamom   bun, and an oat milk latte. I took a sesame sourdough bread home.

⭐️ Absolutely loved the cardamom bun, the texture was soft on the inside and had a sticky glaze on the outside. It wasn’t too sweet. Was 10/10

👅 Did not love the taste of my latte","time":1668712831,"translated":false},{"author_name":"John-Henry Mlyniec","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105361397010892706571/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5TO09rDeEs3bCGbz3uLhCFhgvuzByDJUeUolYO4Tg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"8 months ago","text":"Fantastic experience this morning; my first time visiting the space after being a fan of La Cabra for many years and it did not disappoint. Benny’s (the barista who I mainly interacted with) hospitality was professional, engaging, and fun/down to earth.

Overall the vibe was excellent; truly the best espresso bar experience I’ve had in the USA, and I believe it would do the team back in Copenhagen very proud.

Special varietal Colombia espresso was spot on, and the still hot cardamom bun right out of the oven was unreal!","time":1658788341,"translated":false},{"author_name":"Anton Kovalenko","author_url":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112228773444409275873/reviews","language":"en","original_language":"en","profile_photo_url":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ACB-R5THfKy4-izaenMSTcRltTGaAmVd9l5t2Zbg8u4fIA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4","rating":5,"relative_time_description":"a month ago","text":"Best coffee shop in NY. Being from Portland OR I’m very picky with my coffee. We’ve visited many independent coffee shops throughout the city and haven’t found any other place that takes coffee this seriously. They actually have light/medium roast coffee which was a delight. Their pastures were really delicious as well. I would highly recommend this shop and I plan to stop by again before we head home.","time":1677964383,"translated":false}]
